200class MaximumDurationTracker {
201public:
202 explicit MaximumDurationTracker(double *maxDuration)
203 : m_maxDuration(maxDuration)
204 , m_start(MonotonicTime::now())
205 {
206 }
207
208 ~MaximumDurationTracker()
209 {
210 *m_maxDuration = std::max(*m_maxDuration, (MonotonicTime::now() - m_start).seconds());
211 }
212
213private:
214 double* m_maxDuration;
215 MonotonicTime m_start;
216};

218#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && !ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
219class SyntheticTouchPoint : public PlatformTouchPoint {
220public:
221
222 // The default values are based on http://dvcs.w3.org/hg/webevents/raw-file/tip/touchevents.html
223 explicit SyntheticTouchPoint(const PlatformMouseEvent& event)
224 {
225 static constexpr int idDefaultValue = 0;
226 static constexpr int radiusYDefaultValue = 1;
227 static constexpr int radiusXDefaultValue = 1;
228 static constexpr float rotationAngleDefaultValue = 0.0f;
229 static constexpr float forceDefaultValue = 1.0f;
230
231 m_id = idDefaultValue; // There is only one active TouchPoint.
232 m_screenPos = event.globalPosition();
233 m_pos = event.position();
234 m_radiusY = radiusYDefaultValue;
235 m_radiusX = radiusXDefaultValue;
236 m_rotationAngle = rotationAngleDefaultValue;
237 m_force = forceDefaultValue;
238
239 PlatformEvent::Type type = event.type();
240 ASSERT(type == PlatformEvent::MouseMoved || type == PlatformEvent::MousePressed || type == PlatformEvent::MouseReleased);
241
242 switch (type) {
243 case PlatformEvent::MouseMoved:
244 m_state = TouchMoved;
245 break;
246 case PlatformEvent::MousePressed:
247 m_state = TouchPressed;
248 break;
249 case PlatformEvent::MouseReleased:
250 m_state = TouchReleased;
251 break;
252 default:
253 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
254 break;
255 }
256 }
257};
258
259class SyntheticSingleTouchEvent : public PlatformTouchEvent {
260public:
261 explicit SyntheticSingleTouchEvent(const PlatformMouseEvent& event)
262 {
263 switch (event.type()) {
264 case PlatformEvent::MouseMoved:
265 m_type = TouchMove;
266 break;
267 case PlatformEvent::MousePressed:
268 m_type = TouchStart;
269 break;
270 case PlatformEvent::MouseReleased:
271 m_type = TouchEnd;
272 break;
273 default:
274 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
275 m_type = NoType;
276 break;
277 }
278 m_timestamp = event.timestamp();
279 m_modifiers = event.modifiers();
280 m_touchPoints.append(SyntheticTouchPoint(event));
281 }
282};
283#endif // ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && !ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)

285static inline ScrollGranularity wheelGranularityToScrollGranularity(unsigned deltaMode)
286{
287 switch (deltaMode) {
288 case WheelEvent::DOM_DELTA_PAGE:
289 return ScrollByPage;
290 case WheelEvent::DOM_DELTA_LINE:
291 return ScrollByLine;
292 case WheelEvent::DOM_DELTA_PIXEL:
293 return ScrollByPixel;
294 default:
295 return ScrollByPixel;
296 }
297}

422static void setSelectionIfNeeded(FrameSelection& selection, const VisibleSelection& newSelection)
423{
424 if (selection.selection() != newSelection && selection.shouldChangeSelection(newSelection))
425 selection.setSelection(newSelection);

427
428static inline bool dispatchSelectStart(Node* node)
429{
430 if (!node || !node->renderer())
431 return true;
432
433 auto event = Event::create(eventNames().selectstartEvent, Event::CanBubble::Yes, Event::IsCancelable::Yes);
434 node->dispatchEvent(event);
435 return !event->defaultPrevented();
436}
437
438static Node* nodeToSelectOnMouseDownForNode(Node& targetNode)
439{
440 if (HTMLElement::isInsideImageOverlay(targetNode))
441 return nullptr;
442
443 if (auto rootUserSelectAll = makeRefPtr(Position::rootUserSelectAllForNode(&targetNode)))
444 return rootUserSelectAll.get();
445
446 if (targetNode.shouldSelectOnMouseDown())
447 return &targetNode;
448
449 return nullptr;
450}
451
452static VisibleSelection expandSelectionToRespectSelectOnMouseDown(Node& targetNode, const VisibleSelection& selection)
453{
454 auto nodeToSelect = makeRefPtr(nodeToSelectOnMouseDownForNode(targetNode));
455 if (!nodeToSelect)
456 return selection;
457
458 VisibleSelection newSelection(selection);
459 newSelection.setBase(positionBeforeNode(nodeToSelect.get()).upstream(CanCrossEditingBoundary));
460 newSelection.setExtent(positionAfterNode(nodeToSelect.get()).downstream(CanCrossEditingBoundary));
461
462 return newSelection;
463}
464
465bool EventHandler::updateSelectionForMouseDownDispatchingSelectStart(Node* targetNode, const VisibleSelection& selection, TextGranularity granularity)
466{
467 if (Position::nodeIsUserSelectNone(targetNode))
468 return false;
469
470 if (!dispatchSelectStart(targetNode)) {
471 m_mouseDownMayStartSelect = false;
472 return false;
473 }
474
475 if (selection.isOrphan()) {
476 m_mouseDownMayStartSelect = false;
477 return false;
478 }
479
480 if (selection.isRange())
481 m_selectionInitiationState = ExtendedSelection;
482 else {
483 granularity = TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity;
484 m_selectionInitiationState = PlacedCaret;
485 }
486
487 m_frame.selection().setSelectionByMouseIfDifferent(selection, granularity);
488
489 return true;
490}

492void EventHandler::selectClosestWordFromHitTestResult(const HitTestResult& result, AppendTrailingWhitespace appendTrailingWhitespace)
493{
494 Node* targetNode = result.targetNode();
495 VisibleSelection newSelection;
496
497 if (targetNode && targetNode->renderer()) {
498 VisiblePosition pos(targetNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(result.localPoint(), nullptr));
499 if (pos.isNotNull()) {
500 newSelection = VisibleSelection(pos);
501 newSelection.expandUsingGranularity(TextGranularity::WordGranularity);
502 }
503
504 if (appendTrailingWhitespace == ShouldAppendTrailingWhitespace && newSelection.isRange())
505 newSelection.appendTrailingWhitespace();
506
507 updateSelectionForMouseDownDispatchingSelectStart(targetNode, expandSelectionToRespectSelectOnMouseDown(*targetNode, newSelection), TextGranularity::WordGranularity);
508 }
509}
510
511static AppendTrailingWhitespace shouldAppendTrailingWhitespace(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& result, const Frame& frame)
512{
513 return (result.event().clickCount() == 2 && frame.editor().isSelectTrailingWhitespaceEnabled()) ? ShouldAppendTrailingWhitespace : DontAppendTrailingWhitespace;
514}
515
516void EventHandler::selectClosestWordFromMouseEvent(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& result)
517{
518 if (mouseDownMayStartSelect())
519 selectClosestWordFromHitTestResult(result.hitTestResult(), shouldAppendTrailingWhitespace(result, m_frame));
520}

529void EventHandler::selectClosestContextualWordFromMouseEvent(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& mouseEvent)
530{
531 Node* targetNode = mouseEvent.targetNode();
532 const HitTestResult& result = mouseEvent.hitTestResult();
533 VisibleSelection newSelection;
534 bool appendTrailingWhitespace = shouldAppendTrailingWhitespace(mouseEvent, m_frame);
535
536 if (targetNode && targetNode->renderer()) {
537 newSelection = selectClosestWordFromHitTestResultBasedOnLookup(result);
538 if (newSelection.isNone()) {
539 VisiblePosition pos(targetNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(result.localPoint(), nullptr));
540 if (pos.isNotNull()) {
541 newSelection = VisibleSelection(pos);
542 newSelection.expandUsingGranularity(TextGranularity::WordGranularity);
543 }
544 }
545
546 if (appendTrailingWhitespace == ShouldAppendTrailingWhitespace && newSelection.isRange())
547 newSelection.appendTrailingWhitespace();
548
549 updateSelectionForMouseDownDispatchingSelectStart(targetNode, expandSelectionToRespectSelectOnMouseDown(*targetNode, newSelection), TextGranularity::WordGranularity);
550 }
551}
552
553void EventHandler::selectClosestContextualWordOrLinkFromMouseEvent(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& result)
554{
555 Element* urlElement = result.hitTestResult().URLElement();
556 if (!urlElement || !isDraggableLink(*urlElement)) {
557 if (Node* targetNode = result.targetNode()) {
558 if (isEditableNode(*targetNode))
559 return selectClosestWordFromMouseEvent(result);
560 }
561
562 return selectClosestContextualWordFromMouseEvent(result);
563 }
564
565 Node* targetNode = result.targetNode();
566
567 if (targetNode && targetNode->renderer() && mouseDownMayStartSelect()) {
568 VisibleSelection newSelection;
569 VisiblePosition pos(targetNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(result.localPoint(), nullptr));
570 if (pos.isNotNull() && pos.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()->isDescendantOf(*urlElement))
571 newSelection = VisibleSelection::selectionFromContentsOfNode(urlElement);
572
573 updateSelectionForMouseDownDispatchingSelectStart(targetNode, expandSelectionToRespectSelectOnMouseDown(*targetNode, newSelection), TextGranularity::WordGranularity);
574 }
575}
576
577bool EventHandler::handleMousePressEventDoubleClick(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& event)
578{
579 if (event.event().button() != LeftButton)
580 return false;
581
582 if (m_frame.selection().isRange())
583 // A double-click when range is already selected
584 // should not change the selection. So, do not call
585 // selectClosestWordFromMouseEvent, but do set
586 // m_beganSelectingText to prevent handleMouseReleaseEvent
587 // from setting caret selection.
588 m_selectionInitiationState = ExtendedSelection;
589 else
590 selectClosestWordFromMouseEvent(event);
591
592 return true;
593}
594
595bool EventHandler::handleMousePressEventTripleClick(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& event)
596{
597 if (event.event().button() != LeftButton)
598 return false;
599
600 Node* targetNode = event.targetNode();
601 if (!(targetNode && targetNode->renderer() && mouseDownMayStartSelect()))
602 return false;
603
604 VisibleSelection newSelection;
605 VisiblePosition pos(targetNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(event.localPoint(), nullptr));
606 if (pos.isNotNull()) {
607 newSelection = VisibleSelection(pos);
608 newSelection.expandUsingGranularity(TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity);
609 }
610
611 return updateSelectionForMouseDownDispatchingSelectStart(targetNode, expandSelectionToRespectSelectOnMouseDown(*targetNode, newSelection), TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity);
612}
613
614static uint64_t textDistance(const Position& start, const Position& end)
615{
616 auto range = makeSimpleRange(start, end);
617 if (!range)
618 return 0;
619 return characterCount(*range, TextIteratorBehavior::EmitsCharactersBetweenAllVisiblePositions);
620}
621
622bool EventHandler::handleMousePressEventSingleClick(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& event)
623{
624 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
625
626 m_frame.document()->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
627 Node* targetNode = event.targetNode();
628 if (!targetNode || !targetNode->renderer() || !mouseDownMayStartSelect() || m_mouseDownDelegatedFocus)
629 return false;
630
631 // Extend the selection if the Shift key is down, unless the click is in a link.
632 bool extendSelection = event.event().shiftKey() && !event.isOverLink();
633
634 // Don't restart the selection when the mouse is pressed on an
635 // existing selection so we can allow for text dragging.
636 if (FrameView* view = m_frame.view()) {
637 LayoutPoint vPoint = view->windowToContents(event.event().position());
638 if (!extendSelection && m_frame.selection().contains(vPoint)) {
639 m_mouseDownWasSingleClickInSelection = true;
640 return false;
641 }
642 }
643
644 VisiblePosition visiblePosition(targetNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(event.localPoint(), nullptr));
645 if (visiblePosition.isNull())
646 visiblePosition = VisiblePosition(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(targetNode));
647 Position pos = visiblePosition.deepEquivalent();
648
649 VisibleSelection newSelection = m_frame.selection().selection();
650 TextGranularity granularity = TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity;
651
652 if (!m_frame.editor().client()->shouldAllowSingleClickToChangeSelection(*targetNode, newSelection))
653 return true;
654
655 if (extendSelection && newSelection.isCaretOrRange()) {
656 VisibleSelection selectionInUserSelectAll = expandSelectionToRespectSelectOnMouseDown(*targetNode, VisibleSelection(pos));
657 if (selectionInUserSelectAll.isRange()) {
658 if (selectionInUserSelectAll.start() < newSelection.start())
659 pos = selectionInUserSelectAll.start();
660 else if (newSelection.end() < selectionInUserSelectAll.end())
661 pos = selectionInUserSelectAll.end();
662 }
663
664 if (!m_frame.editor().behavior().shouldConsiderSelectionAsDirectional() && pos.isNotNull()) {
665 // See <rdar://problem/3668157> REGRESSION (Mail): shift-click deselects when selection
666 // was created right-to-left
667 Position start = newSelection.start();
668 Position end = newSelection.end();
669 int distanceToStart = textDistance(start, pos);
670 int distanceToEnd = textDistance(pos, end);
671 if (distanceToStart <= distanceToEnd)
672 newSelection = VisibleSelection(end, pos);
673 else
674 newSelection = VisibleSelection(start, pos);
675 } else
676 newSelection.setExtent(pos);
677
678 if (m_frame.selection().granularity() != TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity) {
679 granularity = m_frame.selection().granularity();
680 newSelection.expandUsingGranularity(m_frame.selection().granularity());
681 }
682 } else {
683 if (event.event().syntheticClickType() != SyntheticClickType::NoTap) {
684 auto adjustedVisiblePosition = wordBoundaryForPositionWithoutCrossingLine(visiblePosition).first;
685 if (adjustedVisiblePosition.isNotNull())
686 visiblePosition = WTFMove(adjustedVisiblePosition);
687 }
688 newSelection = expandSelectionToRespectSelectOnMouseDown(*targetNode, visiblePosition);
689 }
690
691 bool handled = updateSelectionForMouseDownDispatchingSelectStart(targetNode, newSelection, granularity);
692
693 if (event.event().button() == MiddleButton) {
694 // Ignore handled, since we want to paste to where the caret was placed anyway.
695 handled = handlePasteGlobalSelection(event.event()) || handled;
696 }
697 return handled;
698}
699
700bool EventHandler::canMouseDownStartSelect(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& event)
701{
702 auto node = makeRefPtr(event.targetNode());
703
704 if (Page* page = m_frame.page()) {
705 if (!page->chrome().client().shouldUseMouseEventForSelection(event.event()))
706 return false;
707 }
708
709 if (!node || !node->renderer())
710 return true;
711
712 if (HTMLElement::isImageOverlayText(*node))
713 return node->renderer()->style().userSelect() != UserSelect::None;
714
715 return node->canStartSelection() || Position::nodeIsUserSelectAll(node.get());
716}
717
718bool EventHandler::mouseDownMayStartSelect() const
719{
720 if (!m_frame.settings().textInteractionEnabled())
721 return false;
722
723 return m_mouseDownMayStartSelect;
724}
725
726bool EventHandler::handleMousePressEvent(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& event)
727{
728 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
729
730#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
731 // Reset drag state.
732 dragState().source = nullptr;
733#endif
734
735#if !ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
736 cancelFakeMouseMoveEvent();
737#endif
738
739 m_frame.document()->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
740
741 if (ScrollView* scrollView = m_frame.view()) {
742 if (scrollView->isPointInScrollbarCorner(event.event().position()))
743 return false;
744 }
745
746 bool singleClick = event.event().clickCount() <= 1;
747
748 // If we got the event back, that must mean it wasn't prevented,
749 // so it's allowed to start a drag or selection if it wasn't in a scrollbar.
750 m_mouseDownMayStartSelect = canMouseDownStartSelect(event) && !event.scrollbar();
751
752#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
753 // Careful that the drag starting logic stays in sync with eventMayStartDrag()
754 // FIXME: eventMayStartDrag() does not check for shift key press, link or image event targets.
755 // Bug: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=155390
756
757 // Single mouse down on links or images can always trigger drag-n-drop.
758 bool isImageOverlayText = HTMLElement::isImageOverlayText(event.targetNode());
759 bool isMouseDownOnLinkOrImage = event.isOverLink() || (event.hitTestResult().image() && !isImageOverlayText);
760 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = singleClick && (!event.event().shiftKey() || isMouseDownOnLinkOrImage) && shouldAllowMouseDownToStartDrag();
761#endif
762
763 m_mouseDownWasSingleClickInSelection = false;
764
765 m_mouseDownEvent = event.event();
766
767 if (m_immediateActionStage != ImmediateActionStage::PerformedHitTest)
768 m_immediateActionStage = ImmediateActionStage::None;
769
770 if (event.isOverWidget() && passWidgetMouseDownEventToWidget(event))
771 return true;
772
773 if (is<SVGDocument>(*m_frame.document()) && downcast<SVGDocument>(*m_frame.document()).zoomAndPanEnabled()) {
774 if (event.event().shiftKey() && singleClick) {
775 m_svgPan = true;
776 downcast<SVGDocument>(*m_frame.document()).startPan(m_frame.view()->windowToContents(event.event().position()));
777 return true;
778 }
779 }
780
781 // We don't do this at the start of mouse down handling,
782 // because we don't want to do it until we know we didn't hit a widget.
783 if (singleClick)
784 focusDocumentView();
785
786 m_mousePressNode = event.targetNode();
787 m_frame.document()->setFocusNavigationStartingNode(event.targetNode());
788
789#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
790 m_dragStartPosition = event.event().position();
791#endif
792
793 m_mousePressed = true;
794 m_selectionInitiationState = HaveNotStartedSelection;
795
796 bool swallowEvent = false;
797 if (event.event().clickCount() == 2)
798 swallowEvent = handleMousePressEventDoubleClick(event);
799 else if (event.event().clickCount() >= 3)
800 swallowEvent = handleMousePressEventTripleClick(event);
801 else
802 swallowEvent = handleMousePressEventSingleClick(event);
803
804 m_mouseDownMayStartAutoscroll = mouseDownMayStartSelect()
805 || (m_mousePressNode && m_mousePressNode->renderBox() && m_mousePressNode->renderBox()->canBeProgramaticallyScrolled());
806
807 return swallowEvent;
808}
809
810VisiblePosition EventHandler::selectionExtentRespectingEditingBoundary(const VisibleSelection& selection, const LayoutPoint& localPoint, Node* targetNode)
811{
812 FloatPoint selectionEndPoint = localPoint;
813 Element* editableElement = selection.rootEditableElement();
814
815 if (!targetNode || !targetNode->renderer())
816 return VisiblePosition();
817
818 if (editableElement && !editableElement->contains(targetNode)) {
819 if (!editableElement->renderer())
820 return VisiblePosition();
821
822 FloatPoint absolutePoint = targetNode->renderer()->localToAbsolute(FloatPoint(selectionEndPoint));
823 selectionEndPoint = editableElement->renderer()->absoluteToLocal(absolutePoint);
824 targetNode = editableElement;
825 }
826
827 return targetNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(LayoutPoint(selectionEndPoint), nullptr);
828}

846bool EventHandler::handleMouseDraggedEvent(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& event, CheckDragHysteresis checkDragHysteresis)
847{
848 if (!m_mousePressed)
849 return false;
850
851 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
852
853 if (handleDrag(event, checkDragHysteresis))
854 return true;
855
856 Node* targetNode = event.targetNode();
857 if (event.event().button() != LeftButton || !targetNode)
858 return false;
859
860 RenderObject* renderer = targetNode->renderer();
861 if (!renderer) {
862 Element* parent = targetNode->parentOrShadowHostElement();
863 if (!parent)
864 return false;
865
866 renderer = parent->renderer();
867 if (!renderer || !renderer->isListBox())
868 return false;
869 }
870
871#if PLATFORM(COCOA) // FIXME: Why does this assertion fire on other platforms?
872 ASSERT(mouseDownMayStartSelect() || m_mouseDownMayStartAutoscroll);
873#endif
874
875 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = false;
876
877 if (m_mouseDownMayStartAutoscroll && !panScrollInProgress()) {
878 m_autoscrollController->startAutoscrollForSelection(renderer);
879 m_mouseDownMayStartAutoscroll = false;
880 }
881
882 if (m_selectionInitiationState != ExtendedSelection) {
883 HitTestResult result(m_mouseDownContentsPosition);
884 m_frame.document()->hitTest(HitTestRequest(), result);
885
886 updateSelectionForMouseDrag(result);
887 }
888 updateSelectionForMouseDrag(event.hitTestResult());
889 return true;
890}
891
892bool EventHandler::eventMayStartDrag(const PlatformMouseEvent& event) const
893{
894 // This is a pre-flight check of whether the event might lead to a drag being started. Be careful
895 // that its logic needs to stay in sync with handleMouseMoveEvent() and the way we setMouseDownMayStartDrag
896 // in handleMousePressEvent
897 auto* document = m_frame.document();
898 if (!document)
899 return false;
900
901 if (event.button() != LeftButton || event.clickCount() != 1)
902 return false;
903
904 FrameView* view = m_frame.view();
905 if (!view)
906 return false;
907
908 Page* page = m_frame.page();
909 if (!page)
910 return false;
911
912 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
913
914 updateDragSourceActionsAllowed();
915 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent };
916 HitTestResult result(view->windowToContents(event.position()));
917 document->hitTest(hitType, result);
918 DragState state;
919 Element* targetElement = result.targetElement();
920 return targetElement && page->dragController().draggableElement(&m_frame, targetElement, result.roundedPointInInnerNodeFrame(), state);
921}

923void EventHandler::updateSelectionForMouseDrag()
924{
925 if (!supportsSelectionUpdatesOnMouseDrag())
926 return;
927
928 FrameView* view = m_frame.view();
929 if (!view)
930 return;
931 auto* document = m_frame.document();
932 if (!document)
933 return;
934
935 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::Move, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent };
936 HitTestResult result(view->windowToContents(m_lastKnownMousePosition.value_or(IntPoint())));
937 document->hitTest(hitType, result);
938 updateSelectionForMouseDrag(result);
939}
940
941void EventHandler::updateSelectionForMouseDrag(const HitTestResult& hitTestResult)
942{
943 if (!supportsSelectionUpdatesOnMouseDrag())
944 return;
945
946 if (!mouseDownMayStartSelect())
947 return;
948
949 Node* target = hitTestResult.targetNode();
950 if (!target)
951 return;
952
953 if (!HTMLElement::shouldExtendSelectionToTargetNode(*target, m_frame.selection().selection()))
954 return;
955
956 VisiblePosition targetPosition = selectionExtentRespectingEditingBoundary(m_frame.selection().selection(), hitTestResult.localPoint(), target);
957
958 // Don't modify the selection if we're not on a node.
959 if (targetPosition.isNull())
960 return;
961
962 // Restart the selection if this is the first mouse move. This work is usually
963 // done in handleMousePressEvent, but not if the mouse press was on an existing selection.
964 VisibleSelection oldSelection = m_frame.selection().selection();
965 auto newSelection = oldSelection;
966
967 // Special case to limit selection to the containing block for SVG text.
968 // FIXME: Isn't there a better non-SVG-specific way to do this?
969 if (Node* selectionBaseNode = newSelection.base().deprecatedNode()) {
970 if (RenderObject* selectionBaseRenderer = selectionBaseNode->renderer()) {
971 if (selectionBaseRenderer->isSVGText()) {
972 if (target->renderer()->containingBlock() != selectionBaseRenderer->containingBlock())
973 return;
974 }
975 }
976 }
977
978
979 if (m_selectionInitiationState == HaveNotStartedSelection && !dispatchSelectStart(target)) {
980 m_mouseDownMayStartSelect = false;
981 return;
982 }
983
984 if (m_selectionInitiationState != ExtendedSelection) {
985 // Always extend selection here because it's caused by a mouse drag
986 m_selectionInitiationState = ExtendedSelection;
987 newSelection = VisibleSelection(targetPosition);
988 }
989
990 Node* rootUserSelectAllForMousePressNode = Position::rootUserSelectAllForNode(m_mousePressNode.get());
991 if (rootUserSelectAllForMousePressNode && rootUserSelectAllForMousePressNode == Position::rootUserSelectAllForNode(target)) {
992 newSelection.setBase(positionBeforeNode(rootUserSelectAllForMousePressNode).upstream(CanCrossEditingBoundary));
993 newSelection.setExtent(positionAfterNode(rootUserSelectAllForMousePressNode).downstream(CanCrossEditingBoundary));
994 } else {
995 // Reset base for user select all when base is inside user-select-all area and extent < base.
996 if (rootUserSelectAllForMousePressNode && target->renderer()->positionForPoint(hitTestResult.localPoint(), nullptr) < m_mousePressNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(m_dragStartPosition, nullptr))
997 newSelection.setBase(positionAfterNode(rootUserSelectAllForMousePressNode).downstream(CanCrossEditingBoundary));
998
999 Node* rootUserSelectAllForTarget = Position::rootUserSelectAllForNode(target);
1000 if (rootUserSelectAllForTarget && m_mousePressNode->renderer() && target->renderer()->positionForPoint(hitTestResult.localPoint(), nullptr) < m_mousePressNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(m_dragStartPosition, nullptr))
1001 newSelection.setExtent(positionBeforeNode(rootUserSelectAllForTarget).upstream(CanCrossEditingBoundary));
1002 else if (rootUserSelectAllForTarget && m_mousePressNode->renderer())
1003 newSelection.setExtent(positionAfterNode(rootUserSelectAllForTarget).downstream(CanCrossEditingBoundary));
1004 else
1005 newSelection.setExtent(targetPosition);
1006 }
1007
1008 if (m_frame.selection().granularity() != TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity)
1009 newSelection.expandUsingGranularity(m_frame.selection().granularity());
1010
1011 m_frame.selection().setSelectionByMouseIfDifferent(newSelection, m_frame.selection().granularity(),
1012 FrameSelection::EndPointsAdjustmentMode::AdjustAtBidiBoundary);
1013
1014 if (oldSelection != newSelection && HTMLElement::isImageOverlayText(newSelection.start().containerNode()) && HTMLElement::isImageOverlayText(newSelection.end().containerNode()))
1015 invalidateClick();
1016}
1017#endif // ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)

1019void EventHandler::lostMouseCapture()
1020{
1021 m_frame.selection().setCaretBlinkingSuspended(false);
1022}

1024bool EventHandler::handleMouseUp(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& event)
1025{
1026 if (eventLoopHandleMouseUp(event))
1027 return true;
1028
1029 // If this was the first click in the window, we don't even want to clear the selection.
1030 // This case occurs when the user clicks on a draggable element, since we have to process
1031 // the mouse down and drag events to see if we might start a drag. For other first clicks
1032 // in a window, we just don't acceptFirstMouse, and the whole down-drag-up sequence gets
1033 // ignored upstream of this layer.
1034 return eventActivatedView(event.event());
1035}
1036
1037bool EventHandler::handleMouseReleaseEvent(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& event)
1038{
1039 if (autoscrollInProgress())
1040 stopAutoscrollTimer();
1041
1042 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
1043
1044 if (handleMouseUp(event))
1045 return true;
1046
1047 // Used to prevent mouseMoveEvent from initiating a drag before
1048 // the mouse is pressed again.
1049 m_mousePressed = false;
1050 m_capturesDragging = false;
1051#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
1052 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = false;
1053#endif
1054 m_mouseDownMayStartSelect = false;
1055 m_mouseDownMayStartAutoscroll = false;
1056 m_mouseDownWasInSubframe = false;
1057
1058 bool handled = false;
1059
1060 // Clear the selection if the mouse didn't move after the last mouse
1061 // press and it's not a context menu click. We do this so when clicking
1062 // on the selection, the selection goes away. However, if we are
1063 // editing, place the caret.
1064 if (m_mouseDownWasSingleClickInSelection && m_selectionInitiationState != ExtendedSelection
1065#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
1066 && m_dragStartPosition == event.event().position()
1067#endif
1068 && m_frame.selection().isRange()
1069 && event.event().button() != RightButton) {
1070 VisibleSelection newSelection;
1071 Node* node = event.targetNode();
1072 bool caretBrowsing = m_frame.settings().caretBrowsingEnabled();
1073 bool allowSelectionChanges = true;
1074 if (node && node->renderer() && (caretBrowsing || node->hasEditableStyle())) {
1075 VisiblePosition pos = node->renderer()->positionForPoint(event.localPoint(), nullptr);
1076 newSelection = VisibleSelection(pos);
1077#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1078 // On iOS, selection changes are triggered using platform-specific text interaction gestures rather than
1079 // default behavior on click or mouseup. As such, the only time we should allow click events to change the
1080 // selection on iOS is when we focus a different editable element, in which case the text interaction
1081 // gestures will fail.
1082 allowSelectionChanges = m_frame.selection().selection().rootEditableElement() != newSelection.rootEditableElement();
1083#endif
1084 }
1085
1086 if (allowSelectionChanges)
1087 setSelectionIfNeeded(m_frame.selection(), newSelection);
1088
1089 handled = true;
1090 }
1091
1092 if (event.event().button() == MiddleButton) {
1093 // Ignore handled, since we want to paste to where the caret was placed anyway.
1094 handled = handlePasteGlobalSelection(event.event()) || handled;
1095 }
1096
1097 return handled;
1098}

1158
1159HitTestResult EventHandler::hitTestResultAtPoint(const LayoutPoint& point, OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType) const
1160{
1161 ASSERT(!hitType.contains(HitTestRequest::Type::CollectMultipleElements));
1162
1163 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
1164
1165 // We always send hitTestResultAtPoint to the main frame if we have one,
1166 // otherwise we might hit areas that are obscured by higher frames.
1167 if (!m_frame.isMainFrame()) {
1168 Frame& mainFrame = m_frame.mainFrame();
1169 FrameView* frameView = m_frame.view();
1170 FrameView* mainView = mainFrame.view();
1171 if (frameView && mainView) {
1172 IntPoint mainFramePoint = mainView->rootViewToContents(frameView->contentsToRootView(roundedIntPoint(point)));
1173 return mainFrame.eventHandler().hitTestResultAtPoint(mainFramePoint, hitType);
1174 }
1175 }
1176
1177 // We should always start hit testing a clean tree.
1178 if (auto* frameView = m_frame.view())
1179 frameView->updateLayoutAndStyleIfNeededRecursive();
1180
1181 auto result = HitTestResult { point };
1182 auto* document = m_frame.document();
1183 if (!document)
1184 return result;
1185
1186 HitTestRequest request(hitType);
1187 document->hitTest(request, result);
1188 if (!request.readOnly())
1189 m_frame.document()->updateHoverActiveState(request, result.targetElement());
1190
1191 auto innerNode = makeRefPtr(result.innerNode());
1192 if (request.disallowsUserAgentShadowContent()
1193 || (request.disallowsUserAgentShadowContentExceptForImageOverlays() && innerNode && !HTMLElement::isInsideImageOverlay(*innerNode)))
1194 result.setToNonUserAgentShadowAncestor();
1195
1196 return result;
1197}

1204bool EventHandler::scrollOverflow(ScrollDirection direction, ScrollGranularity granularity, Node* startingNode)
1205{
1206 Node* node = startingNode;
1207
1208 if (!node)
1209 node = m_frame.document()->focusedElement();
1210
1211 if (!node)
1212 node = m_mousePressNode.get();
1213
1214 if (node) {
1215 auto r = node->renderer();
1216 if (r && !r->isListBox() && r->enclosingBox().scroll(direction, granularity)) {
1217 setFrameWasScrolledByUser();
1218 return true;
1219 }
1220 }
1221
1222 return false;
1223}

1225bool EventHandler::logicalScrollOverflow(ScrollLogicalDirection direction, ScrollGranularity granularity, Node* startingNode)
1226{
1227 Node* node = startingNode;
1228
1229 if (!node)
1230 node = m_frame.document()->focusedElement();
1231
1232 if (!node)
1233 node = m_mousePressNode.get();
1234
1235 if (node) {
1236 auto r = node->renderer();
1237 if (r && !r->isListBox() && r->enclosingBox().logicalScroll(direction, granularity)) {
1238 setFrameWasScrolledByUser();
1239 return true;
1240 }
1241 }
1242
1243 return false;
1244}

1246bool EventHandler::scrollRecursively(ScrollDirection direction, ScrollGranularity granularity, Node* startingNode)
1247{
1248 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
1249
1250 // The layout needs to be up to date to determine if we can scroll. We may be
1251 // here because of an onLoad event, in which case the final layout hasn't been performed yet.
1252 m_frame.document()->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1253 if (scrollOverflow(direction, granularity, startingNode))
1254 return true;
1255 Frame* frame = &m_frame;
1256 FrameView* view = frame->view();
1257 if (view && view->scroll(direction, granularity))
1258 return true;
1259 frame = frame->tree().parent();
1260 if (!frame)
1261 return false;
1262 return frame->eventHandler().scrollRecursively(direction, granularity, m_frame.ownerElement());
1263}
1264
1265bool EventHandler::logicalScrollRecursively(ScrollLogicalDirection direction, ScrollGranularity granularity, Node* startingNode)
1266{
1267 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
1268
1269 // The layout needs to be up to date to determine if we can scroll. We may be
1270 // here because of an onLoad event, in which case the final layout hasn't been performed yet.
1271 m_frame.document()->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1272 if (logicalScrollOverflow(direction, granularity, startingNode))
1273 return true;
1274 Frame* frame = &m_frame;
1275 FrameView* view = frame->view();
1276
1277 bool scrolled = false;
1278#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
1279 // Mac also resets the scroll position in the inline direction.
1280 if (granularity == ScrollByDocument && view && view->logicalScroll(ScrollInlineDirectionBackward, ScrollByDocument))
1281 scrolled = true;
1282#endif
1283 if (view && view->logicalScroll(direction, granularity))
1284 scrolled = true;
1285
1286 if (scrolled)
1287 return true;
1288
1289 frame = frame->tree().parent();
1290 if (!frame)
1291 return false;
1292
1293 return frame->eventHandler().logicalScrollRecursively(direction, granularity, m_frame.ownerElement());
1294}

1329// Returns true if the node's editable block is not current focused for editing
1330static bool nodeIsNotBeingEdited(const Node& node, const Frame& frame)

1334
1335bool EventHandler::useHandCursor(Node* node, bool isOverLink, bool shiftKey)
1336{
1337 if (!node)
1338 return false;
1339
1340 bool editable = node->hasEditableStyle();
1341 bool editableLinkEnabled = false;
1342
1343 // If the link is editable, then we need to check the settings to see whether or not the link should be followed
1344 if (editable) {
1345 switch (m_frame.settings().editableLinkBehavior()) {
1346 case EditableLinkBehavior::Default:
1347 case EditableLinkBehavior::AlwaysLive:
1348 editableLinkEnabled = true;
1349 break;
1350
1351 case EditableLinkBehavior::NeverLive:
1352 editableLinkEnabled = false;
1353 break;
1354
1355 case EditableLinkBehavior::LiveWhenNotFocused:
1356 editableLinkEnabled = nodeIsNotBeingEdited(*node, m_frame) || shiftKey;
1357 break;
1358
1359 case EditableLinkBehavior::OnlyLiveWithShiftKey:
1360 editableLinkEnabled = shiftKey;
1361 break;
1362 }
1363 }
1364
1365 return ((isOverLink || isSubmitImage(node)) && (!editable || editableLinkEnabled));
1366}

1368void EventHandler::updateCursorIfNeeded()
1369{
1370 if (std::exchange(m_hasScheduledCursorUpdate, false))
1371 updateCursor();
1372}
1373
1374void EventHandler::updateCursor()
1375{
1376 if (!m_lastKnownMousePosition)
1377 return;
1378
1379 if (Page* page = m_frame.page()) {
1380 if (!page->chrome().client().supportsSettingCursor())
1381 return;
1382 }
1383
1384 FrameView* view = m_frame.view();
1385 if (!view)
1386 return;
1387
1388 auto* document = m_frame.document();
1389 if (!document)
1390 return;
1391
1392 if (!view->shouldSetCursor())
1393 return;
1394
1395 bool shiftKey;
1396 bool ctrlKey;
1397 bool altKey;
1398 bool metaKey;
1399 PlatformKeyboardEvent::getCurrentModifierState(shiftKey, ctrlKey, altKey, metaKey);
1400
1401 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::AllowFrameScrollbars };
1402 HitTestResult result(view->windowToContents(*m_lastKnownMousePosition));
1403 document->hitTest(hitType, result);
1404
1405 updateCursor(*view, result, shiftKey);
1406}
1407
1408void EventHandler::updateCursor(FrameView& view, const HitTestResult& result, bool shiftKey)
1409{
1410 if (auto optionalCursor = selectCursor(result, shiftKey)) {
1411 m_currentMouseCursor = WTFMove(optionalCursor.value());
1412 view.setCursor(m_currentMouseCursor);
1413 }
1414}
1415
1416std::optional<Cursor> EventHandler::selectCursor(const HitTestResult& result, bool shiftKey)
1417{
1418 if (m_resizeLayer && m_resizeLayer->inResizeMode())
1419 return std::nullopt;
1420
1421 if (!m_frame.page())
1422 return std::nullopt;
1423
1424#if ENABLE(PAN_SCROLLING)
1425 if (m_frame.mainFrame().eventHandler().panScrollInProgress())
1426 return std::nullopt;
1427#endif
1428
1429 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
1430
1431 // Use always pointer cursor for scrollbars.
1432 if (result.scrollbar()) {
1433#if ENABLE(CURSOR_VISIBILITY)
1434 cancelAutoHideCursorTimer();
1435#endif
1436 return pointerCursor();
1437 }
1438
1439 Node* node = result.targetNode();
1440 if (!node)
1441 return std::nullopt;
1442
1443 auto renderer = node->renderer();
1444 auto* style = renderer ? &renderer->style() : nullptr;
1445 bool horizontalText = !style || style->isHorizontalWritingMode();
1446 const Cursor& iBeam = horizontalText ? iBeamCursor() : verticalTextCursor();
1447
1448#if ENABLE(CURSOR_VISIBILITY)
1449 if (style && style->cursorVisibility() == CursorVisibility::AutoHide)
1450 startAutoHideCursorTimer();
1451 else
1452 cancelAutoHideCursorTimer();
1453#endif
1454
1455 if (renderer) {
1456 Cursor overrideCursor;
1457 switch (renderer->getCursor(roundedIntPoint(result.localPoint()), overrideCursor)) {
1458 case SetCursorBasedOnStyle:
1459 break;
1460 case SetCursor:
1461 return overrideCursor;
1462 case DoNotSetCursor:
1463 return std::nullopt;
1464 }
1465 }
1466
1467 if (style && style->cursors()) {
1468 const CursorList* cursors = style->cursors();
1469 for (unsigned i = 0; i < cursors->size(); ++i) {
1470 StyleImage* styleImage = (*cursors)[i].image();
1471 if (!styleImage)
1472 continue;
1473 CachedImage* cachedImage = styleImage->cachedImage();
1474 if (!cachedImage)
1475 continue;
1476 float scale = styleImage->imageScaleFactor();
1477 // Get hotspot and convert from logical pixels to physical pixels.
1478 IntPoint hotSpot = (*cursors)[i].hotSpot();
1479 FloatSize size = cachedImage->imageForRenderer(renderer)->size();
1480 if (cachedImage->errorOccurred())
1481 continue;
1482 // Limit the size of cursors (in UI pixels) so that they cannot be
1483 // used to cover UI elements in chrome.
1484 size.scale(1 / scale);
1485 if (size.width() > maximumCursorSize || size.height() > maximumCursorSize)
1486 continue;
1487
1488 Image* image = cachedImage->imageForRenderer(renderer);
1489#if ENABLE(MOUSE_CURSOR_SCALE)
1490 // Ensure no overflow possible in calculations above.
1491 if (scale < minimumCursorScale)
1492 continue;
1493 return Cursor(image, hotSpot, scale);
1494#else
1495 ASSERT(scale == 1);
1496 return Cursor(image, hotSpot);
1497#endif // ENABLE(MOUSE_CURSOR_SCALE)
1498 }
1499 }
1500
1501 // During selection, use an I-beam regardless of the content beneath the cursor.
1502 // If a drag may be starting or we're capturing mouse events for a particular node, don't treat this as a selection.
1503 if (m_mousePressed
1504 && mouseDownMayStartSelect()
1505#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
1506 && !m_mouseDownMayStartDrag
1507#endif
1508 && m_frame.selection().isCaretOrRange()
1509 && !m_capturingMouseEventsElement)
1510 return iBeam;
1511
1512 switch (style ? style->cursor() : CursorType::Auto) {
1513 case CursorType::Auto: {
1514 bool editable = node->hasEditableStyle();
1515
1516 if (useHandCursor(node, result.isOverLink(), shiftKey))
1517 return handCursor();
1518
1519 bool inResizer = false;
1520 if (renderer && renderer->hasLayer()) {
1521 // FIXME: With right-aligned text in a box, the renderer here is usually a RenderText, which prevents showing the resize cursor: webkit.org/b/210935.
1522 auto& layerRenderer = downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*renderer);
1523 inResizer = layerRenderer.layer()->isPointInResizeControl(roundedIntPoint(result.localPoint()));
1524 if (inResizer)
1525 return layerRenderer.shouldPlaceVerticalScrollbarOnLeft() ? southWestResizeCursor() : southEastResizeCursor();
1526 }
1527
1528 if ((editable || (renderer && renderer->isText() && node->canStartSelection())) && !inResizer && !result.scrollbar())
1529 return iBeam;
1530 return pointerCursor();
1531 }
1532 case CursorType::Default:
1533 return pointerCursor();
1534 case CursorType::None:
1535 return noneCursor();
1536 case CursorType::ContextMenu:
1537 return contextMenuCursor();
1538 case CursorType::Help:
1539 return helpCursor();
1540 case CursorType::Pointer:
1541 return handCursor();
1542 case CursorType::Progress:
1543 return progressCursor();
1544 case CursorType::Wait:
1545 return waitCursor();
1546 case CursorType::Cell:
1547 return cellCursor();
1548 case CursorType::Crosshair:
1549 return crossCursor();
1550 case CursorType::Text:
1551 return iBeamCursor();
1552 case CursorType::VerticalText:
1553 return verticalTextCursor();
1554 case CursorType::Alias:
1555 return aliasCursor();
1556 case CursorType::Copy:
1557 return copyCursor();
1558 case CursorType::Move:
1559 return moveCursor();
1560 case CursorType::NoDrop:
1561 return noDropCursor();
1562 case CursorType::NotAllowed:
1563 return notAllowedCursor();
1564 case CursorType::Grab:
1565 return grabCursor();
1566 case CursorType::Grabbing:
1567 return grabbingCursor();
1568 case CursorType::EResize:
1569 return eastResizeCursor();
1570 case CursorType::NResize:
1571 return northResizeCursor();
1572 case CursorType::NEResize:
1573 return northEastResizeCursor();
1574 case CursorType::NWResize:
1575 return northWestResizeCursor();
1576 case CursorType::SResize:
1577 return southResizeCursor();
1578 case CursorType::SEResize:
1579 return southEastResizeCursor();
1580 case CursorType::SWResize:
1581 return southWestResizeCursor();
1582 case CursorType::WResize:
1583 return westResizeCursor();
1584 case CursorType::EWResize:
1585 return eastWestResizeCursor();
1586 case CursorType::NSResize:
1587 return northSouthResizeCursor();
1588 case CursorType::NESWResize:
1589 return northEastSouthWestResizeCursor();
1590 case CursorType::NWSEResize:
1591 return northWestSouthEastResizeCursor();
1592 case CursorType::ColumnResize:
1593 return columnResizeCursor();
1594 case CursorType::RowResize:
1595 return rowResizeCursor();
1596 case CursorType::AllScroll:
1597 return moveCursor();
1598 case CursorType::ZoomIn:
1599 return zoomInCursor();
1600 case CursorType::ZoomOut:
1601 return zoomOutCursor();
1602 }
1603 return pointerCursor();
1604}

1608{
1609 Page* page = m_frame.page();
1610 if (!page)
1611 return;
1612
1613 m_autoHideCursorTimer.startOneShot(page->settings().timeWithoutMouseMovementBeforeHidingControls());
1614
1615#if !ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)

1617 // so cancel any pending fake mouse moves.
1618 if (m_fakeMouseMoveEventTimer.isActive())
1619 m_fakeMouseMoveEventTimer.stop();
1620#endif

1636 page->chrome().setCursorHiddenUntilMouseMoves(true);
1637}

1640static LayoutPoint documentPointForWindowPoint(Frame& frame, const IntPoint& windowPoint)
1641{
1642 FrameView* view = frame.view();
1643 // FIXME: Is it really OK to use the wrong coordinates here when view is 0?
1644 // Historically the code would just crash; this is clearly no worse than that.
1645 return view ? view->windowToContents(windowPoint) : windowPoint;
1646}

1649{
1650 if (view) {
1651 if (auto* scrollbar = view->scrollbarAtPoint(mouseEvent.event().position()))
1652 return scrollbar;
1653 }
1654 return mouseEvent.scrollbar();

1657
1658bool EventHandler::handleMousePressEvent(const PlatformMouseEvent& platformMouseEvent)
1659{
1660 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
1661 RefPtr<FrameView> protector(m_frame.view());
1662
1663 if (InspectorInstrumentation::handleMousePress(m_frame)) {
1664 invalidateClick();
1665 return true;
1666 }
1667
1668#if ENABLE(POINTER_LOCK)
1669 if (m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().isLocked()) {
1670 m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().dispatchLockedMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent, eventNames().mousedownEvent);
1671 return true;
1672 }
1673#endif
1674
1675 if (m_frame.page()->pageOverlayController().handleMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent))
1676 return true;
1677
1678#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
1679 bool defaultPrevented = dispatchSyntheticTouchEventIfEnabled(platformMouseEvent);
1680 if (defaultPrevented)
1681 return true;
1682#endif
1683
1684 UserGestureIndicator gestureIndicator(ProcessingUserGesture, m_frame.document());
1685
1686 // FIXME (bug 68185): this call should be made at another abstraction layer
1687 m_frame.loader().resetMultipleFormSubmissionProtection();
1688
1689#if !ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
1690 cancelFakeMouseMoveEvent();
1691#endif
1692 m_mousePressed = true;
1693 m_capturesDragging = true;
1694 setLastKnownMousePosition(platformMouseEvent);
1695 m_mouseDownTimestamp = platformMouseEvent.timestamp();
1696#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
1697 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = false;
1698#endif
1699 m_mouseDownMayStartSelect = false;
1700 m_mouseDownMayStartAutoscroll = false;
1701 if (FrameView* view = m_frame.view())
1702 m_mouseDownContentsPosition = view->windowToContents(platformMouseEvent.position());
1703 else {
1704 invalidateClick();
1705 return false;
1706 }
1707 m_mouseDownWasInSubframe = false;
1708
1709 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent };
1710 // Save the document point we generate in case the window coordinate is invalidated by what happens
1711 // when we dispatch the event.
1712 LayoutPoint documentPoint = documentPointForWindowPoint(m_frame, platformMouseEvent.position());
1713 MouseEventWithHitTestResults mouseEvent = m_frame.document()->prepareMouseEvent(hitType, documentPoint, platformMouseEvent);
1714
1715 if (!mouseEvent.targetNode()) {
1716 invalidateClick();
1717 return false;
1718 }
1719
1720 m_mousePressNode = mouseEvent.targetNode();
1721 m_frame.document()->setFocusNavigationStartingNode(mouseEvent.targetNode());
1722
1723 Scrollbar* scrollbar = scrollbarForMouseEvent(mouseEvent, m_frame.view());
1724 updateLastScrollbarUnderMouse(scrollbar, SetOrClearLastScrollbar::Set);
1725 bool passedToScrollbar = scrollbar && passMousePressEventToScrollbar(mouseEvent, scrollbar);
1726
1727 if (!passedToScrollbar) {
1728 RefPtr<Frame> subframe = subframeForHitTestResult(mouseEvent);
1729 if (subframe && passMousePressEventToSubframe(mouseEvent, *subframe)) {
1730 // Start capturing future events for this frame. We only do this if we didn't clear
1731 // the m_mousePressed flag, which may happen if an AppKit widget entered a modal event loop.
1732 m_capturesDragging = subframe->eventHandler().capturesDragging();
1733 if (m_mousePressed && m_capturesDragging) {
1734 m_capturingMouseEventsElement = subframe->ownerElement();
1735 m_eventHandlerWillResetCapturingMouseEventsElement = true;
1736 }
1737 invalidateClick();
1738 return true;
1739 }
1740 }
1741
1742#if ENABLE(PAN_SCROLLING)
1743 // We store whether pan scrolling is in progress before calling stopAutoscrollTimer()
1744 // because it will set m_autoscrollType to NoAutoscroll on return.
1745 bool isPanScrollInProgress = m_frame.mainFrame().eventHandler().panScrollInProgress();
1746 stopAutoscrollTimer();
1747 if (isPanScrollInProgress) {
1748 // We invalidate the click when exiting pan scrolling so that we don't inadvertently navigate
1749 // away from the current page (e.g. the click was on a hyperlink). See <rdar://problem/6095023>.
1750 invalidateClick();
1751 return true;
1752 }
1753#endif
1754
1755 m_clickCount = platformMouseEvent.clickCount();
1756 m_clickNode = mouseEvent.targetNode();
1757
1758 if (!m_clickNode) {
1759 invalidateClick();
1760 return false;
1761 }
1762
1763 RenderLayer* layer = m_clickNode->renderer() ? m_clickNode->renderer()->enclosingLayer() : nullptr;
1764 auto localPoint = roundedIntPoint(mouseEvent.hitTestResult().localPoint());
1765 if (layer && layer->isPointInResizeControl(localPoint)) {
1766 layer->setInResizeMode(true);
1767 m_resizeLayer = layer;
1768 m_offsetFromResizeCorner = layer->offsetFromResizeCorner(localPoint);
1769 invalidateClick();
1770 return true;
1771 }
1772
1773 m_frame.selection().setCaretBlinkingSuspended(true);
1774
1775 bool swallowEvent = !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().mousedownEvent, mouseEvent.targetNode(), m_clickCount, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::Yes);
1776 if (auto page = m_frame.page(); page && swallowEvent)
1777 page->chrome().client().didHandleOrPreventMouseDownOrMouseUpEvent();
1778 m_capturesDragging = !swallowEvent || mouseEvent.scrollbar();
1779
1780 // If the hit testing originally determined the event was in a scrollbar, refetch the MouseEventWithHitTestResults
1781 // in case the scrollbar widget was destroyed when the mouse event was handled.
1782 if (mouseEvent.scrollbar()) {
1783 const bool wasLastScrollBar = mouseEvent.scrollbar() == m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse;
1784 mouseEvent = m_frame.document()->prepareMouseEvent(HitTestRequest(), documentPoint, platformMouseEvent);
1785 if (wasLastScrollBar && mouseEvent.scrollbar() != m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse)
1786 m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse = nullptr;
1787 }
1788
1789 if (!swallowEvent) {
1790 // Refetch the event target node if it currently is the shadow node inside an <input> element.
1791 // If a mouse event handler changes the input element type to one that has a widget associated,
1792 // we'd like to EventHandler::handleMousePressEvent to pass the event to the widget and thus the
1793 // event target node can't still be the shadow node.
1794 if (is<ShadowRoot>(*mouseEvent.targetNode()) && is<HTMLInputElement>(*downcast<ShadowRoot>(*mouseEvent.targetNode()).host()))
1795 mouseEvent = m_frame.document()->prepareMouseEvent(HitTestRequest(), documentPoint, platformMouseEvent);
1796 }
1797
1798 if (!swallowEvent) {
1799 if (passedToScrollbar)
1800 swallowEvent = true;
1801 else
1802 swallowEvent = handleMousePressEvent(mouseEvent);
1803 }
1804 return swallowEvent;
1805}
1806
1807// This method only exists for platforms that don't know how to deliver
1808bool EventHandler::handleMouseDoubleClickEvent(const PlatformMouseEvent& platformMouseEvent)
1809{
1810 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
1811 RefPtr<FrameView> protector(m_frame.view());
1812
1813 m_frame.selection().setCaretBlinkingSuspended(false);
1814
1815 UserGestureIndicator gestureIndicator(ProcessingUserGesture, m_frame.document());
1816
1817#if ENABLE(POINTER_LOCK)
1818 if (m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().isLocked()) {
1819 m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().dispatchLockedMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent, eventNames().mouseupEvent);
1820 return true;
1821 }
1822#endif
1823
1824 // We get this instead of a second mouse-up
1825 m_mousePressed = false;
1826 setLastKnownMousePosition(platformMouseEvent);
1827
1828 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::Release, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent };
1829 MouseEventWithHitTestResults mouseEvent = prepareMouseEvent(hitType, platformMouseEvent);
1830 auto subframe = subframeForHitTestResult(mouseEvent);
1831
1832 if (m_eventHandlerWillResetCapturingMouseEventsElement)
1833 m_capturingMouseEventsElement = nullptr;
1834
1835 if (subframe && passMousePressEventToSubframe(mouseEvent, *subframe))
1836 return true;
1837
1838 m_clickCount = platformMouseEvent.clickCount();
1839 bool swallowMouseUpEvent = !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().mouseupEvent, mouseEvent.targetNode(), m_clickCount, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::No);
1840 if (auto page = m_frame.page(); page && swallowMouseUpEvent)
1841 page->chrome().client().didHandleOrPreventMouseDownOrMouseUpEvent();
1842
1843 bool swallowClickEvent = platformMouseEvent.button() != RightButton && mouseEvent.targetNode() == m_clickNode && !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().clickEvent, mouseEvent.targetNode(), m_clickCount, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::Yes);
1844
1845 if (m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse)
1846 swallowMouseUpEvent = m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse->mouseUp(platformMouseEvent);
1847
1848 bool swallowMouseReleaseEvent = !swallowMouseUpEvent && handleMouseReleaseEvent(mouseEvent);
1849
1850 invalidateClick();
1851
1852 return swallowMouseUpEvent || swallowClickEvent || swallowMouseReleaseEvent;
1853}
1854
1855ScrollableArea* EventHandler::enclosingScrollableArea(Node* node)
1856{
1857 for (auto ancestor = node; ancestor; ancestor = ancestor->parentOrShadowHostNode()) {
1858 if (is<HTMLIFrameElement>(*ancestor))
1859 return nullptr;
1860
1861 if (is<HTMLHtmlElement>(*ancestor) || is<HTMLDocument>(*ancestor))
1862 break;
1863
1864 auto renderer = ancestor->renderer();
1865 if (!renderer)
1866 continue;
1867
1868 if (is<RenderListBox>(*renderer)) {
1869 auto* scrollableArea = static_cast<ScrollableArea*>(downcast<RenderListBox>(renderer));
1870 if (scrollableArea->isScrollableOrRubberbandable())
1871 return scrollableArea;
1872 }
1873
1874 auto* layer = renderer->enclosingLayer();
1875 if (!layer)
1876 return nullptr;
1877
1878 if (auto* scrollableLayer = layer->enclosingScrollableLayer(IncludeSelfOrNot::IncludeSelf, CrossFrameBoundaries::No)) {
1879 if (!scrollableLayer->isRenderViewLayer())
1880 return scrollableLayer->scrollableArea();
1881 }
1882 }
1883
1884 return m_frame.view();
1885}
1886
1887bool EventHandler::mouseMoved(const PlatformMouseEvent& event)
1888{
1889 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
1890 RefPtr<FrameView> protector(m_frame.view());
1891 MaximumDurationTracker maxDurationTracker(&m_maxMouseMovedDuration);
1892
1893 if (m_frame.page() && m_frame.page()->pageOverlayController().handleMouseEvent(event))
1894 return true;
1895
1896 HitTestResult hitTestResult;
1897 bool result = handleMouseMoveEvent(event, &hitTestResult);
1898
1899 Page* page = m_frame.page();
1900 if (!page)
1901 return result;
1902
1903 hitTestResult.setToNonUserAgentShadowAncestor();
1904 page->chrome().mouseDidMoveOverElement(hitTestResult, event.modifierFlags());
1905
1906#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
1907 if (event.syntheticClickType() == NoTap && m_textRecognitionHoverTimer.isActive())
1908 m_textRecognitionHoverTimer.restart();
1909#endif
1910
1911 return result;
1912}
1913
1914bool EventHandler::passMouseMovedEventToScrollbars(const PlatformMouseEvent& event)
1915{
1916 HitTestResult hitTestResult;
1917 return handleMouseMoveEvent(event, &hitTestResult, true);
1918}
1919
1920bool EventHandler::handleMouseMoveEvent(const PlatformMouseEvent& platformMouseEvent, HitTestResult* hitTestResult, bool onlyUpdateScrollbars)
1921{
1922#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
1923 bool defaultPrevented = dispatchSyntheticTouchEventIfEnabled(platformMouseEvent);
1924 if (defaultPrevented)
1925 return true;
1926#endif
1927
1928 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
1929 RefPtr<FrameView> protector(m_frame.view());
1930
1931#if ENABLE(POINTER_LOCK)
1932 if (m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().isLocked()) {
1933 m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().dispatchLockedMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent, eventNames().mousemoveEvent);
1934 return true;
1935 }
1936#endif
1937
1938 setLastKnownMousePosition(platformMouseEvent);
1939
1940 if (m_hoverTimer.isActive())
1941 m_hoverTimer.stop();
1942
1943 m_hasScheduledCursorUpdate = false;
1944
1945#if !ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
1946 cancelFakeMouseMoveEvent();
1947#endif
1948
1949 if (m_svgPan) {
1950 downcast<SVGDocument>(*m_frame.document()).updatePan(m_frame.view()->windowToContents(m_lastKnownMousePosition.value_or(IntPoint())));
1951 return true;
1952 }
1953
1954 if (m_frameSetBeingResized)
1955 return !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().mousemoveEvent, m_frameSetBeingResized.get(), 0, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::No);
1956
1957 // On iOS, our scrollbars are managed by UIKit.
1958#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1959 // Send events right to a scrollbar if the mouse is pressed.
1960 if (m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse && m_mousePressed)
1961 return m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse->mouseMoved(platformMouseEvent);
1962#endif
1963
1964 OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::Move, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent, HitTestRequest::Type::AllowFrameScrollbars };
1965 if (m_mousePressed)
1966 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::Active);
1967 else if (onlyUpdateScrollbars) {
1968 // Mouse events should be treated as "read-only" if we're updating only scrollbars. This
1969 // means that :hover and :active freeze in the state they were in, rather than updating
1970 // for nodes the mouse moves while the window is not key (which will be the case if
1971 // onlyUpdateScrollbars is true).
1972 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly);
1973 }
1974
1975#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && !ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
1976 // Treat any mouse move events as readonly if the user is currently touching the screen.
1977 if (m_touchPressed) {
1978 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::Active);
1979 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly);
1980 }
1981#endif
1982 HitTestRequest request(hitType);
1983 MouseEventWithHitTestResults mouseEvent = prepareMouseEvent(request, platformMouseEvent);
1984 if (hitTestResult)
1985 *hitTestResult = mouseEvent.hitTestResult();
1986
1987 if (m_resizeLayer && m_resizeLayer->inResizeMode())
1988 m_resizeLayer->resize(platformMouseEvent, m_offsetFromResizeCorner);
1989 else {
1990 Scrollbar* scrollbar = mouseEvent.scrollbar();
1991 updateLastScrollbarUnderMouse(scrollbar, m_mousePressed ? SetOrClearLastScrollbar::Clear : SetOrClearLastScrollbar::Set);
1992
1993 // On iOS, our scrollbars are managed by UIKit.
1994#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1995 if (!m_mousePressed && scrollbar)
1996 scrollbar->mouseMoved(platformMouseEvent); // Handle hover effects on platforms that support visual feedback on scrollbar hovering.
1997#endif
1998 if (onlyUpdateScrollbars) {
1999 if (shouldSendMouseEventsToInactiveWindows())
2000 updateMouseEventTargetNode(eventNames().mousemoveEvent, mouseEvent.targetNode(), platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::Yes);
2001
2002 return true;
2003 }
2004 }
2005
2006 bool swallowEvent = false;
2007 RefPtr<Frame> newSubframe = m_capturingMouseEventsElement.get() ? subframeForTargetNode(m_capturingMouseEventsElement.get()) : subframeForHitTestResult(mouseEvent);
2008
2009 // We want mouseouts to happen first, from the inside out. First send a move event to the last subframe so that it will fire mouseouts.
2010 if (m_lastMouseMoveEventSubframe && m_lastMouseMoveEventSubframe->tree().isDescendantOf(&m_frame) && m_lastMouseMoveEventSubframe != newSubframe)
2011 passMouseMoveEventToSubframe(mouseEvent, *m_lastMouseMoveEventSubframe);
2012
2013 if (newSubframe) {
2014 // Update over/out state before passing the event to the subframe.
2015 updateMouseEventTargetNode(eventNames().mousemoveEvent, mouseEvent.targetNode(), platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::Yes);
2016
2017 // Event dispatch in updateMouseEventTargetNode may have caused the subframe of the target
2018 // node to be detached from its FrameView, in which case the event should not be passed.
2019 if (newSubframe->view())
2020 swallowEvent |= passMouseMoveEventToSubframe(mouseEvent, *newSubframe, hitTestResult);
2021 }
2022
2023 if (!newSubframe || mouseEvent.scrollbar()) {
2024 if (auto* view = m_frame.view())
2025 updateCursor(*view, mouseEvent.hitTestResult(), platformMouseEvent.shiftKey());
2026 }
2027
2028 m_lastMouseMoveEventSubframe = newSubframe;
2029
2030 if (swallowEvent)
2031 return true;
2032
2033 swallowEvent = !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().mousemoveEvent, mouseEvent.targetNode(), 0, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::Yes);
2034
2035#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
2036 if (!swallowEvent)
2037 swallowEvent = handleMouseDraggedEvent(mouseEvent);
2038#endif
2039
2040 return swallowEvent;
2041}

2056
2057static RefPtr<Node> targetNodeForClickEvent(Node* mousePressNode, Node* mouseReleaseNode)
2058{
2059 if (!mousePressNode || !mouseReleaseNode)
2060 return nullptr;
2061
2062 if (mousePressNode == mouseReleaseNode)
2063 return mouseReleaseNode;
2064
2065 // If mousePressNode and mouseReleaseNode differ, we should fire the event at their common ancestor if there is one.
2066 if (&mousePressNode->document() == &mouseReleaseNode->document()) {
2067 if (auto commonAncestor = commonInclusiveAncestor<ComposedTree>(*mousePressNode, *mouseReleaseNode))
2068 return commonAncestor;
2069 }
2070
2071 auto mouseReleaseShadowHost = mouseReleaseNode->shadowHost();
2072 if (mouseReleaseShadowHost && mouseReleaseShadowHost == mousePressNode->shadowHost()) {
2073 // We want to dispatch the click to the shadow tree host element to give listeners the illusion that the
2074 // shadom tree is a single element. For example, we want to give the illusion that <input type="range">
2075 // is a single element even though it is a composition of multiple shadom tree elements.
2076 return mouseReleaseShadowHost;
2077 }
2078
2079 return nullptr;
2080}

2082bool EventHandler::handleMouseReleaseEvent(const PlatformMouseEvent& platformMouseEvent)
2083{
2084 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
2085 RefPtr<FrameView> protector(m_frame.view());
2086
2087 m_frame.selection().setCaretBlinkingSuspended(false);
2088
2089#if ENABLE(POINTER_LOCK)
2090 if (m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().isLocked()) {
2091 m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().dispatchLockedMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent, eventNames().mouseupEvent);
2092 return true;
2093 }
2094#endif
2095
2096 if (m_frame.page()->pageOverlayController().handleMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent))
2097 return true;
2098
2099#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
2100 bool defaultPrevented = dispatchSyntheticTouchEventIfEnabled(platformMouseEvent);
2101 if (defaultPrevented)
2102 return true;
2103#endif
2104
2105 UserGestureIndicator gestureIndicator(ProcessingUserGesture, m_frame.document());
2106
2107#if ENABLE(PAN_SCROLLING)
2108 m_autoscrollController->handleMouseReleaseEvent(platformMouseEvent);
2109#endif
2110
2111 m_mousePressed = false;
2112 setLastKnownMousePosition(platformMouseEvent);
2113
2114 if (m_svgPan) {
2115 m_svgPan = false;
2116 downcast<SVGDocument>(*m_frame.document()).updatePan(m_frame.view()->windowToContents(m_lastKnownMousePosition.value_or(IntPoint())));
2117 return true;
2118 }
2119
2120 if (m_frameSetBeingResized)
2121 return !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().mouseupEvent, m_frameSetBeingResized.get(), m_clickCount, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::No);
2122
2123 // If an immediate action began or was completed using this series of mouse events, then we should send mouseup to
2124 // the DOM and return now so that we don't perform our own default behaviors.
2125 if (m_immediateActionStage == ImmediateActionStage::ActionCompleted || m_immediateActionStage == ImmediateActionStage::ActionUpdated || m_immediateActionStage == ImmediateActionStage::ActionCancelledAfterUpdate) {
2126 m_immediateActionStage = ImmediateActionStage::None;
2127 return !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().mouseupEvent, m_lastElementUnderMouse.get(), m_clickCount, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::No);
2128 }
2129 m_immediateActionStage = ImmediateActionStage::None;
2130
2131 if (m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse) {
2132 invalidateClick();
2133 m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse->mouseUp(platformMouseEvent);
2134 return !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().mouseupEvent, m_lastElementUnderMouse.get(), m_clickCount, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::No);
2135 }
2136
2137 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::Release, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent };
2138 MouseEventWithHitTestResults mouseEvent = prepareMouseEvent(hitType, platformMouseEvent);
2139 RefPtr<Frame> subframe = m_capturingMouseEventsElement.get() ? subframeForTargetNode(m_capturingMouseEventsElement.get()) : subframeForHitTestResult(mouseEvent);
2140 if (m_eventHandlerWillResetCapturingMouseEventsElement)
2141 m_capturingMouseEventsElement = nullptr;
2142 if (subframe && passMouseReleaseEventToSubframe(mouseEvent, *subframe))
2143 return true;
2144
2145 bool swallowMouseUpEvent = !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().mouseupEvent, mouseEvent.targetNode(), m_clickCount, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::No);
2146 if (auto page = m_frame.page(); page && swallowMouseUpEvent)
2147 page->chrome().client().didHandleOrPreventMouseDownOrMouseUpEvent();
2148
2149 bool contextMenuEvent = platformMouseEvent.button() == RightButton;
2150
2151 auto nodeToClick = targetNodeForClickEvent(m_clickNode.get(), mouseEvent.targetNode());
2152 bool swallowClickEvent = m_clickCount > 0 && !contextMenuEvent && nodeToClick && !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().clickEvent, nodeToClick.get(), m_clickCount, platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut::Yes);
2153
2154 if (m_resizeLayer) {
2155 m_resizeLayer->setInResizeMode(false);
2156 m_resizeLayer = nullptr;
2157 }
2158
2159 bool swallowMouseReleaseEvent = false;
2160 if (!swallowMouseUpEvent)
2161 swallowMouseReleaseEvent = handleMouseReleaseEvent(mouseEvent);
2162
2163 invalidateClick();
2164
2165 return swallowMouseUpEvent || swallowClickEvent || swallowMouseReleaseEvent;
2166}

2209bool EventHandler::handlePasteGlobalSelection(const PlatformMouseEvent& platformMouseEvent)
2210{
2211 // If the event was a middle click, attempt to copy global selection in after
2212 // the newly set caret position.
2213 //
2214 // This code is called from either the mouse up or mouse down handling. There
2215 // is some debate about when the global selection is pasted:
2216 // xterm: pastes on up.
2217 // GTK: pastes on down.
2218 // Qt: pastes on up.
2219 // Firefox: pastes on up.
2220 // Chromium: pastes on up.
2221 //
2222 // There is something of a webcompat angle to this well, as highlighted by
2223 // crbug.com/14608. Pages can clear text boxes 'onclick' and, if we paste on
2224 // down then the text is pasted just before the onclick handler runs and
2225 // clears the text box. So it's important this happens after the event
2226 // handlers have been fired.
2227#if PLATFORM(GTK)
2228 if (platformMouseEvent.type() != PlatformEvent::MousePressed)
2229 return false;
2230#else
2231 if (platformMouseEvent.type() != PlatformEvent::MouseReleased)
2232 return false;
2233#endif
2234
2235 if (!m_frame.page())
2236 return false;
2237 Frame& focusFrame = m_frame.page()->focusController().focusedOrMainFrame();
2238 // Do not paste here if the focus was moved somewhere else.
2239 if (&m_frame == &focusFrame && m_frame.editor().client()->supportsGlobalSelection())
2240 return m_frame.editor().command("PasteGlobalSelection"_s).execute();
2241
2242 return false;
2243}

2248{
2249 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
2250 FrameView* view = m_frame.view();
2251
2252 // FIXME: We might want to dispatch a dragleave even if the view is gone.

2254 return false;

2256 auto dragEvent = DragEvent::create(eventType, Event::CanBubble::Yes, Event::IsCancelable::Yes, Event::IsComposed::Yes,
2257 event.timestamp().approximateMonotonicTime(), &m_frame.windowProxy(), 0,
2258 event.globalPosition(), event.position(),
2259#if ENABLE(POINTER_LOCK)
2260 event.movementDelta(),
2261#else
2262 { },
2263#endif

2265
2266 dragTarget.dispatchEvent(dragEvent);
2267
2268 if (auto* cache = m_frame.document()->existingAXObjectCache()) {
2269 if (eventType == eventNames().dragstartEvent)
2270 cache->postNotification(&dragTarget, AXObjectCache::AXDraggingStarted);
2271 else if (eventType == eventNames().dragendEvent)

2273 else if (eventType == eventNames().dragenterEvent)

2275 else if (eventType == eventNames().dragleaveEvent)
2276 cache->postNotification(&dragTarget, AXObjectCache::AXDraggingExitedDropZone);
2277 else if (eventType == eventNames().dropEvent)

2281 return dragEvent->defaultPrevented();

2298static std::optional<DragOperation> convertDropZoneOperationToDragOperation(const String& dragOperation)
2299{
2300 if (dragOperation == "copy")
2301 return DragOperation::Copy;
2302 if (dragOperation == "move")
2303 return DragOperation::Move;
2304 if (dragOperation == "link")
2305 return DragOperation::Link;
2306 return std::nullopt;

2309static String convertDragOperationToDropZoneOperation(std::optional<DragOperation> operation)
2310{
2311 if (operation) {
2312 switch (*operation) {
2313 case DragOperation::Move:
2314 return "move"_s;
2315 case DragOperation::Link:
2316 return "link"_s;
2317 default:
2318 break;
2319 }
2320 }
2321 return "copy"_s;

2324static bool hasDropZoneType(DataTransfer& dataTransfer, const String& keyword)
2325{
2326 if (keyword.startsWith("file:"))
2327 return dataTransfer.hasFileOfType(keyword.substring(5));
2328
2329 if (keyword.startsWith("string:"))
2330 return dataTransfer.hasStringOfType(keyword.substring(7));
2331
2332 return false;
2333}
2334
2335static bool findDropZone(Node& target, DataTransfer& dataTransfer)
2336{
2337 RefPtr<Element> element = is<Element>(target) ? &downcast<Element>(target) : target.parentElement();
2338 for (; element; element = element->parentElement()) {
2339 SpaceSplitString keywords(element->attributeWithoutSynchronization(webkitdropzoneAttr), true);
2340 bool matched = false;
2341 std::optional<DragOperation> dragOperation;
2342 for (unsigned i = 0, size = keywords.size(); i < size; ++i) {
2343 if (auto operationFromKeyword = convertDropZoneOperationToDragOperation(keywords[i])) {
2344 if (!dragOperation)
2345 dragOperation = operationFromKeyword;
2346 } else
2347 matched = matched || hasDropZoneType(dataTransfer, keywords[i].string());
2348 if (matched && dragOperation)
2349 break;
2350 }
2351 if (matched) {
2352 dataTransfer.setDropEffect(convertDragOperationToDropZoneOperation(dragOperation));
2353 return true;
2354 }
2355 }
2356 return false;
2357}

2359EventHandler::DragTargetResponse EventHandler::dispatchDragEnterOrDragOverEvent(const AtomString& eventType, Element& target, const PlatformMouseEvent& event, std::unique_ptr<Pasteboard>&& pasteboard, OptionSet<DragOperation> sourceOperationMask, bool draggingFiles)
2360{
2361 auto dataTransfer = DataTransfer::createForUpdatingDropTarget(target.document(), WTFMove(pasteboard), sourceOperationMask, draggingFiles);
2362 bool accept = dispatchDragEvent(eventType, target, event, dataTransfer.get());
2363 if (!accept)
2364 accept = findDropZone(target, dataTransfer);
2365 dataTransfer->makeInvalidForSecurity();
2366 if (accept && !dataTransfer->dropEffectIsUninitialized())
2367 return { true, dataTransfer->destinationOperationMask() };
2368 return { accept, std::nullopt };

2370
2371EventHandler::DragTargetResponse EventHandler::updateDragAndDrop(const PlatformMouseEvent& event, const std::function<std::unique_ptr<Pasteboard>()>& makePasteboard, OptionSet<DragOperation> sourceOperationMask, bool draggingFiles)
2372{
2373 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
2374 if (!m_frame.view())
2375 return { };
2376
2377 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent };
2378 MouseEventWithHitTestResults mouseEvent = prepareMouseEvent(hitType, event);
2379
2380 RefPtr<Element> newTarget;
2381 if (Node* targetNode = mouseEvent.targetNode()) {
2382 // Drag events should never go to non-element nodes (following IE, and proper mouseover/out dispatch)
2383 if (!is<Element>(*targetNode))
2384 newTarget = targetNode->parentOrShadowHostElement();
2385 else
2386 newTarget = downcast<Element>(targetNode);
2387 }
2388
2389 m_autoscrollController->updateDragAndDrop(newTarget.get(), event.position(), event.timestamp());
2390
2391 DragTargetResponse response;
2392 if (m_dragTarget != newTarget) {
2393 // FIXME: this ordering was explicitly chosen to match WinIE. However,
2394 // it is sometimes incorrect when dragging within subframes, as seen with
2395 // LayoutTests/fast/events/drag-in-frames.html.
2396 //
2397 // Moreover, this ordering conforms to section 7.9.4 of the HTML 5 spec. <http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec/Overview.html#drag-and-drop-processing-model>.
2398 Frame* targetFrame;
2399 if (targetIsFrame(newTarget.get(), targetFrame)) {
2400 if (targetFrame)
2401 response = targetFrame->eventHandler().updateDragAndDrop(event, makePasteboard, sourceOperationMask, draggingFiles);
2402 } else if (newTarget) {
2403 // As per section 7.9.4 of the HTML 5 spec., we must always fire a drag event before firing a dragenter, dragleave, or dragover event.
2404 dispatchEventToDragSourceElement(eventNames().dragEvent, event);
2405 response = dispatchDragEnterOrDragOverEvent(eventNames().dragenterEvent, *newTarget, event, makePasteboard(), sourceOperationMask, draggingFiles);
2406 }
2407
2408 if (targetIsFrame(m_dragTarget.get(), targetFrame)) {
2409 // FIXME: Recursing again here doesn't make sense if the newTarget and m_dragTarget were in the same frame.
2410 if (targetFrame)
2411 response = targetFrame->eventHandler().updateDragAndDrop(event, makePasteboard, sourceOperationMask, draggingFiles);
2412 } else if (m_dragTarget) {
2413 auto dataTransfer = DataTransfer::createForUpdatingDropTarget(m_dragTarget->document(), makePasteboard(), sourceOperationMask, draggingFiles);
2414 dispatchDragEvent(eventNames().dragleaveEvent, *m_dragTarget, event, dataTransfer.get());
2415 dataTransfer->makeInvalidForSecurity();
2416 }
2417
2418 if (newTarget) {
2419 // We do not explicitly call dispatchDragEvent here because it could ultimately result in the appearance that
2420 // two dragover events fired. So, we mark that we should only fire a dragover event on the next call to this function.
2421 m_shouldOnlyFireDragOverEvent = true;
2422 }
2423 } else {
2424 Frame* targetFrame;
2425 if (targetIsFrame(newTarget.get(), targetFrame)) {
2426 if (targetFrame)
2427 response = targetFrame->eventHandler().updateDragAndDrop(event, makePasteboard, sourceOperationMask, draggingFiles);
2428 } else if (newTarget) {
2429 // Note, when dealing with sub-frames, we may need to fire only a dragover event as a drag event may have been fired earlier.
2430 if (!m_shouldOnlyFireDragOverEvent)
2431 dispatchEventToDragSourceElement(eventNames().dragEvent, event);
2432 response = dispatchDragEnterOrDragOverEvent(eventNames().dragoverEvent, *newTarget, event, makePasteboard(), sourceOperationMask, draggingFiles);
2433 m_shouldOnlyFireDragOverEvent = false;
2434 }
2435 }
2436 m_dragTarget = WTFMove(newTarget);
2437 return response;
2438}

2440void EventHandler::cancelDragAndDrop(const PlatformMouseEvent& event, std::unique_ptr<Pasteboard>&& pasteboard, OptionSet<DragOperation> sourceOperationMask, bool draggingFiles)

2522
2523void EventHandler::updateMouseEventTargetNode(const AtomString& eventType, Node* targetNode, const PlatformMouseEvent& platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut fireMouseOverOut)
2524{
2525 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
2526 Element* targetElement = nullptr;
2527
2528 // If we're capturing, we always go right to that element.
2529 if (m_capturingMouseEventsElement)
2530 targetElement = m_capturingMouseEventsElement.get();
2531 else if (targetNode) {
2532 // If the target node is a non-element, dispatch on the parent. <rdar://problem/4196646>
2533 while (targetNode && !is<Element>(*targetNode))
2534 targetNode = targetNode->parentInComposedTree();
2535 targetElement = downcast<Element>(targetNode);
2536 }
2537
2538 m_elementUnderMouse = targetElement;
2539
2540#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
2541 if (m_frame.settings().preferInlineTextSelectionInImages()) {
2542 if (!m_elementUnderMouse || !is<RenderImage>(m_elementUnderMouse->renderer()))
2543 m_textRecognitionHoverTimer.stop();
2544 else if (!platformMouseEvent.movementDelta().isZero())
2545 m_textRecognitionHoverTimer.restart();
2546 }
2547#endif // ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
2548
2549 if (auto* page = m_frame.page())
2550 page->imageOverlayController().elementUnderMouseDidChange(m_frame, m_elementUnderMouse.get());
2551
2552 ASSERT_IMPLIES(m_elementUnderMouse, &m_elementUnderMouse->document() == m_frame.document());
2553 ASSERT_IMPLIES(m_lastElementUnderMouse, &m_lastElementUnderMouse->document() == m_frame.document());
2554
2555 // Fire mouseout/mouseover if the mouse has shifted to a different node.
2556 if (fireMouseOverOut == FireMouseOverOut::Yes) {
2557 notifyScrollableAreasOfMouseEvents(eventType, m_lastElementUnderMouse.get(), m_elementUnderMouse.get());
2558
2559 if (m_lastElementUnderMouse && &m_lastElementUnderMouse->document() != m_frame.document()) {
2560 m_lastElementUnderMouse = nullptr;
2561 m_lastScrollbarUnderMouse = nullptr;
2562 }
2563
2564 if (m_lastElementUnderMouse != m_elementUnderMouse) {
2565 // mouseenter and mouseleave events are only dispatched if there is a capturing eventhandler on an ancestor
2566 // or a normal eventhandler on the element itself (they don't bubble).
2567 // This optimization is necessary since these events can cause O(n^2) capturing event-handler checks.
2568 bool hasCapturingMouseEnterListener = hierarchyHasCapturingEventListeners(m_elementUnderMouse.get(), eventNames().pointerenterEvent, eventNames().mouseenterEvent);
2569 bool hasCapturingMouseLeaveListener = hierarchyHasCapturingEventListeners(m_lastElementUnderMouse.get(), eventNames().pointerleaveEvent, eventNames().mouseleaveEvent);
2570
2571 Vector<Ref<Element>, 32> leftElementsChain;
2572 for (Element* element = m_lastElementUnderMouse.get(); element; element = element->parentElementInComposedTree())
2573 leftElementsChain.append(*element);
2574 Vector<Ref<Element>, 32> enteredElementsChain;
2575 for (Element* element = m_elementUnderMouse.get(); element; element = element->parentElementInComposedTree())
2576 enteredElementsChain.append(*element);
2577
2578 if (!leftElementsChain.isEmpty() && !enteredElementsChain.isEmpty() && leftElementsChain.last().ptr() == enteredElementsChain.last().ptr()) {
2579 size_t minHeight = std::min(leftElementsChain.size(), enteredElementsChain.size());
2580 size_t i;
2581 for (i = 0; i < minHeight; ++i) {
2582 if (leftElementsChain[leftElementsChain.size() - i - 1].ptr() != enteredElementsChain[enteredElementsChain.size() - i - 1].ptr())
2583 break;
2584 }
2585 leftElementsChain.shrink(leftElementsChain.size() - i);
2586 enteredElementsChain.shrink(enteredElementsChain.size() - i);
2587 }
2588
2589 if (auto lastElementUnderMouse = m_lastElementUnderMouse)
2590 lastElementUnderMouse->dispatchMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent, eventNames().mouseoutEvent, 0, m_elementUnderMouse.get());
2591
2592 for (auto& chain : leftElementsChain) {
2593 if (hasCapturingMouseLeaveListener || chain->hasEventListeners(eventNames().pointerleaveEvent) || chain->hasEventListeners(eventNames().mouseleaveEvent))
2594 chain->dispatchMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent, eventNames().mouseleaveEvent, 0, m_elementUnderMouse.get());
2595 }
2596
2597 if (auto elementUnderMouse = m_elementUnderMouse)
2598 elementUnderMouse->dispatchMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent, eventNames().mouseoverEvent, 0, m_lastElementUnderMouse.get());
2599
2600 for (auto& chain : WTF::makeReversedRange(enteredElementsChain)) {
2601 if (hasCapturingMouseEnterListener || chain->hasEventListeners(eventNames().pointerenterEvent) || chain->hasEventListeners(eventNames().mouseenterEvent))
2602 chain->dispatchMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent, eventNames().mouseenterEvent, 0, m_lastElementUnderMouse.get());
2603 }
2604 }
2605
2606 // Event handling may have moved the element to a different document.
2607 if (m_elementUnderMouse && &m_elementUnderMouse->document() != m_frame.document()) {
2608#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
2609 m_textRecognitionHoverTimer.stop();
2610#endif
2611 clearElementUnderMouse();
2612 }
2613
2614 m_lastElementUnderMouse = m_elementUnderMouse;
2615 }
2616}
