2636void EventHandler::notifyScrollableAreasOfMouseEvents(const AtomString& eventType, Element* lastElementUnderMouse, Element* elementUnderMouse)
2637{
2638 auto* frameView = m_frame.view();
2639 if (!frameView)
2640 return;
2641
2642 auto scrollableAreaForLastNode = enclosingScrollableArea(lastElementUnderMouse);
2643 auto scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse = enclosingScrollableArea(elementUnderMouse);
2644
2645 if (!!lastElementUnderMouse != !!elementUnderMouse) {
2646 if (elementUnderMouse) {
2647 if (scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse != frameView)
2648 frameView->mouseEnteredContentArea();
2649
2650 if (scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse)
2651 scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse->mouseEnteredContentArea();
2652 } else {
2653 if (scrollableAreaForLastNode)
2654 scrollableAreaForLastNode->mouseExitedContentArea();
2655
2656 if (scrollableAreaForLastNode != frameView)
2657 frameView->mouseExitedContentArea();
2658 }
2659 return;
2660 }
2661
2662 if (!scrollableAreaForLastNode && !scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse)
2663 return;
2664
2665 // FIXME: This does doesn't handle nested ScrollableAreas well. It really needs to know
2666 // the hierarchical relationship between scrollableAreaForLastNode and scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse.
2667 bool movedBetweenScrollableaAreas = scrollableAreaForLastNode && scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse && (scrollableAreaForLastNode != scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse);
2668 if (eventType == eventNames().mousemoveEvent) {
2669 frameView->mouseMovedInContentArea();
2670
2671 if (!movedBetweenScrollableaAreas && scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse && scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse != frameView)
2672 scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse->mouseMovedInContentArea();
2673 }
2674
2675 if (!movedBetweenScrollableaAreas)
2676 return;
2677
2678 if (scrollableAreaForLastNode && scrollableAreaForLastNode != frameView)
2679 scrollableAreaForLastNode->mouseExitedContentArea();
2680
2681 if (scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse && scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse != frameView)
2682 scrollableAreaForNodeUnderMouse->mouseEnteredContentArea();
2683}

2685static RefPtr<Element> findFirstMouseFocusableElementInComposedTree(Element& host)
2686{
2687 ASSERT(host.shadowRoot());
2688 for (auto& node : composedTreeDescendants(host)) {
2689 if (!is<Element>(node))
2690 continue;
2691 auto& element = downcast<Element>(node);
2692 if (element.isMouseFocusable())
2693 return &element;
2694 }
2695 return nullptr;

2698bool EventHandler::dispatchMouseEvent(const AtomString& eventType, Node* targetNode, int clickCount, const PlatformMouseEvent& platformMouseEvent, FireMouseOverOut fireMouseOverOut)
2699{
2700 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
2701
2702 updateMouseEventTargetNode(eventType, targetNode, platformMouseEvent, fireMouseOverOut);
2703
2704 if (auto elementUnderMouse = m_elementUnderMouse) {
2705 if (!elementUnderMouse->dispatchMouseEvent(platformMouseEvent, eventType, clickCount))
2706 return false;
2707 }
2708
2709 if (eventType != eventNames().mousedownEvent)
2710 return true;
2711
2712 m_mouseDownDelegatedFocus = false;
2713
2714 // If clicking on a frame scrollbar, do not make any change to which element is focused.
2715 auto* view = m_frame.view();
2716 if (view && view->scrollbarAtPoint(platformMouseEvent.position()))
2717 return true;
2718
2719 // The layout needs to be up to date to determine if an element is focusable.
2720 m_frame.document()->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
2721
2722 // Remove focus from the currently focused element when a link or button is clicked.
2723 // This is expected by some sites that rely on change event handlers running
2724 // from form fields before the button click is processed, behavior that was inherited
2725 // from the user interface of Windows, where pushing a button moves focus to the button.
2726
2727 // Walk up the DOM tree to search for an element to focus.
2728 RefPtr<Element> element;
2729 for (element = m_elementUnderMouse.get(); element; element = element->parentElementInComposedTree()) {
2730 if (auto* shadowRoot = element->shadowRoot()) {
2731 if (shadowRoot->delegatesFocus()) {
2732 element = findFirstMouseFocusableElementInComposedTree(*element);
2733 m_mouseDownDelegatedFocus = true;
2734 break;
2735 }
2736 }
2737 if (element->isMouseFocusable())
2738 break;
2739 }
2740
2741 // To fix <rdar://problem/4895428> Can't drag selected ToDo, we don't focus an
2742 // element on mouse down if it's selected and inside a focused element. It will be
2743 // focused if the user does a mouseup over it, however, because the mouseup
2744 // will set a selection inside it, which will also set the focused element.
2745 if (element && m_frame.selection().isRange()) {
2746 if (auto range = m_frame.selection().selection().toNormalizedRange()) {
2747 if (contains<ComposedTree>(*range, *element) && element->isDescendantOf(m_frame.document()->focusedElement()))
2748 return true;
2749 }
2750 }
2751
2752 // Only change the focus when clicking scrollbars if it can be transferred to a mouse focusable node.
2753 if (!element && isInsideScrollbar(platformMouseEvent.position()))
2754 return false;
2755
2756 // If focus shift is blocked, we eat the event.
2757 auto* page = m_frame.page();
2758 if (page && !page->focusController().setFocusedElement(element.get(), m_frame, { { }, { }, { }, FocusTrigger::Click, { } }))
2759 return false;
2760
2761 if (element && m_mouseDownDelegatedFocus)
2762 element->findTargetAndUpdateFocusAppearance(SelectionRestorationMode::SelectAll);
2763
2764 return true;
2765}

2772 return result.scrollbar();

2902bool EventHandler::handleWheelEventInternal(const PlatformWheelEvent& event, OptionSet<WheelEventProcessingSteps> processingSteps, OptionSet<EventHandling>& handling)
2903{
2904 auto* document = m_frame.document();
2905 if (!document)
2906 return false;
2907
2908 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
2909 RefPtr<FrameView> protector(m_frame.view());
2910
2911 FrameView* view = m_frame.view();
2912 if (!view)
2913 return false;
2914
2915 if (!m_frame.page())
2916 return false;
2917
2918#if ENABLE(POINTER_LOCK)
2919 if (m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().isLocked()) {
2920 m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().dispatchLockedWheelEvent(event);
2921 return true;
2922 }
2923#endif
2924
2925#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
2926 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "EventHandler::handleWheelEvent " << event << " processing steps " << processingSteps);
2927 auto monitor = m_frame.page()->wheelEventTestMonitor();
2928 if (monitor)
2929 monitor->receivedWheelEvent(event);
2930
2931 auto deferrer = WheelEventTestMonitorCompletionDeferrer { monitor.get(), this, WheelEventTestMonitor::DeferReason::HandlingWheelEventOnMainThread };
2932#endif
2933
2934 m_isHandlingWheelEvent = true;
2935 auto allowsScrollingState = SetForScope(m_currentWheelEventAllowsScrolling, processingSteps.contains(WheelEventProcessingSteps::MainThreadForScrolling));
2936
2937 setFrameWasScrolledByUser();
2938
2939 if (m_frame.isMainFrame()) {
2940#if ENABLE(WHEEL_EVENT_LATCHING)
2941 m_frame.page()->scrollLatchingController().receivedWheelEvent(event);
2942#endif
2943 recordWheelEventForDeltaFilter(event);
2944 }
2945
2946 HitTestRequest request;
2947 HitTestResult result(view->windowToContents(event.position()));
2948 document->hitTest(request, result);
2949
2950 RefPtr<Element> element = result.targetElement();
2951 WeakPtr<ScrollableArea> scrollableArea;
2952 bool isOverWidget = result.isOverWidget();
2953
2954 // FIXME: Despite doing this up-front search for the correct scrollable area, we dispatch events via elements which
2955 // itself finds and tries to scroll overflow scrollers.
2956 determineWheelEventTarget(event, element, scrollableArea, isOverWidget);
2957
2958 if (element) {
2959 if (isOverWidget) {
2960 if (WeakPtr<Widget> widget = widgetForElement(*element)) {
2961 if (passWheelEventToWidget(event, *widget.get(), processingSteps))
2962 return completeWidgetWheelEvent(event, widget, scrollableArea);
2963 }
2964 }
2965
2966 auto isCancelable = processingSteps.contains(WheelEventProcessingSteps::MainThreadForBlockingDOMEventDispatch) ? Event::IsCancelable::Yes : Event::IsCancelable::No;
2967 if (!element->dispatchWheelEvent(event, handling, isCancelable)) {
2968 m_isHandlingWheelEvent = false;
2969 if (scrollableArea && scrollableArea->scrollShouldClearLatchedState()) {
2970 // Web developer is controlling scrolling, so don't attempt to latch.
2971 if (handling.containsAll({ EventHandling::DispatchedToDOM, EventHandling::DefaultPrevented }))
2972 clearLatchedState();
2973 scrollableArea->setScrollShouldClearLatchedState(false);
2974 }
2975
2976 processWheelEventForScrollSnap(event, scrollableArea);
2977 return true;
2978 }
2979 }
2980
2981 if (scrollableArea)
2982 scrollableArea->setScrollShouldClearLatchedState(false);
2983
2984 // Event handling may have disconnected m_frame.
2985 if (!m_frame.page())
2986 return false;
2987
2988 bool handledEvent = false;
2989 bool allowScrolling = m_currentWheelEventAllowsScrolling;
2990
2991#if ENABLE(WHEEL_EVENT_LATCHING)
2992 if (allowScrolling)
2993 allowScrolling = m_frame.page()->scrollLatchingController().latchingAllowsScrollingInFrame(m_frame, scrollableArea);
2994#endif
2995
2996 if (allowScrolling) {
2997 // FIXME: processWheelEventForScrolling() is only called for FrameView scrolling, not overflow scrolling, which is confusing.
2998 handledEvent = processWheelEventForScrolling(event, scrollableArea, handling);
2999 processWheelEventForScrollSnap(event, scrollableArea);
3000 }
3001
3002 return handledEvent;
3003}

3016static bool didScrollInScrollableArea(ScrollableArea& scrollableArea, const WheelEvent& wheelEvent)
3017{
3018 ScrollGranularity scrollGranularity = wheelGranularityToScrollGranularity(wheelEvent.deltaMode());
3019 bool didHandleWheelEvent = false;
3020 if (float absoluteDelta = std::abs(wheelEvent.deltaX()))
3021 didHandleWheelEvent |= scrollableArea.scroll(wheelEvent.deltaX() > 0 ? ScrollRight : ScrollLeft, scrollGranularity, absoluteDelta);
3022
3023 if (float absoluteDelta = std::abs(wheelEvent.deltaY()))
3024 didHandleWheelEvent |= scrollableArea.scroll(wheelEvent.deltaY() > 0 ? ScrollDown : ScrollUp, scrollGranularity, absoluteDelta);
3025
3026 return didHandleWheelEvent;
3027}

3029bool EventHandler::handleWheelEventInAppropriateEnclosingBox(Node* startNode, const WheelEvent& wheelEvent, const FloatSize& filteredPlatformDelta, const FloatSize& filteredVelocity, OptionSet<EventHandling> eventHandling)
3030{
3031 bool shouldHandleEvent = wheelEvent.deltaX() || wheelEvent.deltaY();
3032#if ENABLE(WHEEL_EVENT_LATCHING)
3033 shouldHandleEvent |= wheelEvent.phase() == PlatformWheelEventPhase::Ended;
3034 shouldHandleEvent |= wheelEvent.momentumPhase() == PlatformWheelEventPhase::Ended;
3035#endif
3036 if (!startNode->renderer())
3037 return false;
3038
3039 RenderBox& initialEnclosingBox = startNode->renderer()->enclosingBox();
3040
3041 // RenderListBox is special because it's a ScrollableArea that the scrolling tree doesn't know about.
3042 if (is<RenderListBox>(initialEnclosingBox))
3043 handleWheelEventPhaseInScrollableArea(downcast<RenderListBox>(initialEnclosingBox), wheelEvent);
3044
3045 if (!shouldHandleEvent)
3046 return false;
3047
3048 if (is<RenderListBox>(initialEnclosingBox))
3049 return didScrollInScrollableArea(downcast<RenderListBox>(initialEnclosingBox), wheelEvent);
3050
3051 RenderBox* currentEnclosingBox = &initialEnclosingBox;
3052 while (currentEnclosingBox) {
3053 if (auto* boxLayer = currentEnclosingBox->layer() ? currentEnclosingBox->layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr) {
3054 auto platformEvent = wheelEvent.underlyingPlatformEvent();
3055 bool scrollingWasHandled;
3056 if (platformEvent) {
3057 auto copiedEvent = platformEvent->copyWithDeltasAndVelocity(filteredPlatformDelta.width(), filteredPlatformDelta.height(), filteredVelocity);
3058 scrollingWasHandled = handleWheelEventInScrollableArea(copiedEvent, *boxLayer, eventHandling);
3059 } else
3060 scrollingWasHandled = didScrollInScrollableArea(*boxLayer, wheelEvent);
3061
3062 if (scrollingWasHandled)
3063 return true;
3064 }
3065
3066 currentEnclosingBox = currentEnclosingBox->containingBlock();
3067 if (!currentEnclosingBox || currentEnclosingBox->isRenderView())
3068 return false;
3069 }
3070 return false;
3071}

3076 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "EventHandler::handleWheelEventInScrollableArea() " << scrollableArea << " - eventHandling " << eventHandling << " -> gesture state " << gestureState);
3077 return scrollableArea.handleWheelEventForScrolling(wheelEvent, gestureState);

3109void EventHandler::defaultWheelEventHandler(Node* startNode, WheelEvent& wheelEvent)
3110{
3111 if (!startNode)
3112 return;
3113
3114 if (!m_frame.page())
3115 return;
3116
3117 auto platformEvent = wheelEvent.underlyingPlatformEvent();
3118 bool isUserEvent = platformEvent.has_value();
3119
3120 if (isUserEvent && !m_currentWheelEventAllowsScrolling)
3121 return;
3122
3123 auto protectedFrame = makeRef(m_frame);
3124
3125 FloatSize filteredPlatformDelta(wheelEvent.deltaX(), wheelEvent.deltaY());
3126 FloatSize filteredVelocity;
3127 if (auto platformWheelEvent = wheelEvent.underlyingPlatformEvent()) {
3128 filteredPlatformDelta.setWidth(platformWheelEvent->deltaX());
3129 filteredPlatformDelta.setHeight(platformWheelEvent->deltaY());
3130 }
3131
3132 OptionSet<EventHandling> eventHandling = { EventHandling::DispatchedToDOM };
3133 if (wheelEvent.defaultPrevented())

3135
3136#if ENABLE(WHEEL_EVENT_LATCHING)

3139 filteredVelocity = m_frame.page()->wheelEventDeltaFilter()->filteredVelocity();
3140 }
3141
3142 WeakPtr<ScrollableArea> latchedScroller;
3143 if (!m_frame.page()->scrollLatchingController().latchingAllowsScrollingInFrame(m_frame, latchedScroller))
3144 return;
3145

3147 if (latchedScroller == m_frame.view()) {
3148 // FrameView scrolling is handled via processWheelEventForScrolling().
3149 return;
3150 }
3151
3152 if (platformEvent) {
3153 auto copiedEvent = platformEvent->copyWithDeltasAndVelocity(filteredPlatformDelta.width(), filteredPlatformDelta.height(), filteredVelocity);
3154 if (handleWheelEventInScrollableArea(copiedEvent, *latchedScroller, eventHandling))
3155 wheelEvent.setDefaultHandled();

3158 }
3159#endif

3165#if ENABLE(CONTEXT_MENU_EVENT)
3166bool EventHandler::sendContextMenuEvent(const PlatformMouseEvent& event)
3167{
3168 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
3169
3170 Document* doc = m_frame.document();
3171 FrameView* view = m_frame.view();
3172 if (!view)
3173 return false;
3174
3175 // Caret blinking is normally un-suspended in handleMouseReleaseEvent, but we
3176 // won't receive that event once the context menu is up.
3177 m_frame.selection().setCaretBlinkingSuspended(false);
3178 // Clear mouse press state to avoid initiating a drag while context menu is up.
3179 m_mousePressed = false;
3180 bool swallowEvent;
3181 LayoutPoint viewportPos = view->windowToContents(event.position());
3182 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent };
3183 MouseEventWithHitTestResults mouseEvent = doc->prepareMouseEvent(hitType, viewportPos, event);
3184
3185 // Do not show context menus when clicking on scrollbars.
3186 if (mouseEvent.scrollbar() || view->scrollbarAtPoint(event.position()))
3187 return false;
3188
3189 if (m_frame.editor().behavior().shouldSelectOnContextualMenuClick()
3190 && !m_frame.selection().contains(viewportPos)
3191 // FIXME: In the editable case, word selection sometimes selects content that isn't underneath the mouse.
3192 // If the selection is non-editable, we do word selection to make it easier to use the contextual menu items
3193 // available for text selections. But only if we're above text.
3194 && (m_frame.selection().selection().isContentEditable() || (mouseEvent.targetNode() && mouseEvent.targetNode()->isTextNode()))) {
3195 m_mouseDownMayStartSelect = true; // context menu events are always allowed to perform a selection
3196 selectClosestContextualWordOrLinkFromMouseEvent(mouseEvent);
3197 }
3198
3199 swallowEvent = !dispatchMouseEvent(eventNames().contextmenuEvent, mouseEvent.targetNode(), 0, event, FireMouseOverOut::No);
3200
3201 return swallowEvent;
3202}
3203
3204bool EventHandler::sendContextMenuEventForKey()
3205{
3206 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
3207
3208 FrameView* view = m_frame.view();
3209 if (!view)
3210 return false;
3211
3212 Document* doc = m_frame.document();
3213 if (!doc)
3214 return false;
3215
3216 // Clear mouse press state to avoid initiating a drag while context menu is up.
3217 m_mousePressed = false;
3218
3219 static const int kContextMenuMargin = 1;
3220
3221#if OS(WINDOWS)
3222 int rightAligned = ::GetSystemMetrics(SM_MENUDROPALIGNMENT);
3223#else
3224 int rightAligned = 0;
3225#endif
3226 IntPoint location;
3227
3228 Element* focusedElement = doc->focusedElement();
3229 const VisibleSelection& selection = m_frame.selection().selection();
3230 Position start = selection.start();
3231
3232 if (start.deprecatedNode() && (selection.rootEditableElement() || selection.isRange())) {
3233 IntRect firstRect = m_frame.editor().firstRectForRange(*selection.toNormalizedRange());
3234
3235 int x = rightAligned ? firstRect.maxX() : firstRect.x();
3236 // In a multiline edit, firstRect.maxY() would endup on the next line, so -1.
3237 int y = firstRect.maxY() ? firstRect.maxY() - 1 : 0;
3238 location = IntPoint(x, y);
3239 } else if (focusedElement) {
3240 RenderBoxModelObject* box = focusedElement->renderBoxModelObject();
3241 if (!box)
3242 return false;
3243
3244 IntRect boundingBoxRect = box->absoluteBoundingBoxRect(true);
3245 location = IntPoint(boundingBoxRect.x(), boundingBoxRect.maxY() - 1);
3246 } else {
3247 location = IntPoint(
3248 rightAligned ? view->contentsWidth() - kContextMenuMargin : kContextMenuMargin,
3249 kContextMenuMargin);
3250 }
3251
3252 m_frame.view()->setCursor(pointerCursor());
3253
3254 IntPoint position = view->contentsToRootView(location);
3255 IntPoint globalPosition = view->hostWindow()->rootViewToScreen(IntRect(position, IntSize())).location();
3256
3257 Node* targetNode = doc->focusedElement();
3258 if (!targetNode)
3259 targetNode = doc;
3260
3261 // Use the focused node as the target for hover and active.
3262 HitTestResult result(position);
3263 result.setInnerNode(targetNode);
3264 doc->updateHoverActiveState(OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> { HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent }, result.targetElement());
3265
3266 // The contextmenu event is a mouse event even when invoked using the keyboard.
3267 // This is required for web compatibility.
3268
3269#if OS(WINDOWS)
3270 PlatformEvent::Type eventType = PlatformEvent::MouseReleased;
3271#else
3272 PlatformEvent::Type eventType = PlatformEvent::MousePressed;
3273#endif
3274
3275 PlatformMouseEvent platformMouseEvent(position, globalPosition, RightButton, eventType, 1, false, false, false, false, WallTime::now(), ForceAtClick, NoTap);
3276
3277 return sendContextMenuEvent(platformMouseEvent);
3278}
3279#endif // ENABLE(CONTEXT_MENU_EVENT)

3412bool EventHandler::handleAccessKey(const PlatformKeyboardEvent& event)
3413{
3414 // FIXME: Ignoring the state of Shift key is what neither IE nor Firefox do.
3415 // IE matches lower and upper case access keys regardless of Shift key state - but if both upper and
3416 // lower case variants are present in a document, the correct element is matched based on Shift key state.
3417 // Firefox only matches an access key if Shift is not pressed, and does that case-insensitively.
3418 ASSERT(!accessKeyModifiers().contains(PlatformEvent::Modifier::ShiftKey));
3419
3420 if ((event.modifiers() - PlatformEvent::Modifier::ShiftKey) != accessKeyModifiers())
3421 return false;
3422 auto* element = m_frame.document()->elementForAccessKey(event.unmodifiedText());
3423 if (!element)
3424 return false;
3425 element->accessKeyAction(false);
3426 return true;
3427}

3437bool EventHandler::isKeyEventAllowedInFullScreen(const PlatformKeyboardEvent& keyEvent) const
3438{

3458bool EventHandler::keyEvent(const PlatformKeyboardEvent& keyEvent)
3459{
3460 Document* topDocument = m_frame.document() ? &m_frame.document()->topDocument() : nullptr;
3461 MonotonicTime savedLastHandledUserGestureTimestamp;
3462 bool savedUserDidInteractWithPage = topDocument ? topDocument->userDidInteractWithPage() : false;
3463
3464 if (m_frame.document())
3465 savedLastHandledUserGestureTimestamp = m_frame.document()->lastHandledUserGestureTimestamp();
3466
3467 bool wasHandled = internalKeyEvent(keyEvent);
3468
3469 // If the key event was not handled, do not treat it as user interaction with the page.
3470 if (topDocument) {
3471 if (!wasHandled)
3472 topDocument->setUserDidInteractWithPage(savedUserDidInteractWithPage);
3473 else
3474 ResourceLoadObserver::shared().logUserInteractionWithReducedTimeResolution(*topDocument);
3475 }
3476
3477 if (!wasHandled && m_frame.document())
3478 m_frame.document()->updateLastHandledUserGestureTimestamp(savedLastHandledUserGestureTimestamp);
3479
3480 return wasHandled;
3481}

3490
3491bool EventHandler::internalKeyEvent(const PlatformKeyboardEvent& initialKeyEvent)
3492{
3493 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
3494 RefPtr<FrameView> protector(m_frame.view());
3495
3496 LOG(Editing, "EventHandler %p keyEvent (text %s keyIdentifier %s)", this, initialKeyEvent.text().utf8().data(), initialKeyEvent.keyIdentifier().utf8().data());
3497
3498#if ENABLE(POINTER_LOCK)
3499 if (initialKeyEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::KeyDown && initialKeyEvent.windowsVirtualKeyCode() == VK_ESCAPE && m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().element()) {
3500 m_frame.page()->pointerLockController().requestPointerUnlockAndForceCursorVisible();
3501 }
3502#endif
3503
3504 if (initialKeyEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::KeyDown && initialKeyEvent.windowsVirtualKeyCode() == VK_ESCAPE) {
3505 if (auto* page = m_frame.page()) {
3506 if (auto* validationMessageClient = page->validationMessageClient())
3507 validationMessageClient->hideAnyValidationMessage();
3508 }
3509 }
3510
3511#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
3512 if (m_frame.document()->fullscreenManager().isFullscreen()) {
3513 if (initialKeyEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::KeyDown && initialKeyEvent.windowsVirtualKeyCode() == VK_ESCAPE) {
3514 m_frame.document()->fullscreenManager().cancelFullscreen();
3515 return true;
3516 }
3517
3518 if (!isKeyEventAllowedInFullScreen(initialKeyEvent))
3519 return false;
3520 }
3521#endif
3522
3523 if (initialKeyEvent.windowsVirtualKeyCode() == VK_CAPITAL)
3524 capsLockStateMayHaveChanged();
3525
3526#if ENABLE(PAN_SCROLLING)
3527 if (m_frame.mainFrame().eventHandler().panScrollInProgress()) {
3528 // If a key is pressed while the panScroll is in progress then we want to stop
3529 if (initialKeyEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::KeyDown || initialKeyEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::RawKeyDown)
3530 stopAutoscrollTimer();
3531
3532 // If we were in panscroll mode, we swallow the key event
3533 return true;
3534 }
3535#endif
3536
3537 // Check for cases where we are too early for events -- possible unmatched key up
3538 // from pressing return in the location bar.
3539 RefPtr<Element> element = eventTargetElementForDocument(m_frame.document());
3540 if (!element)
3541 return false;
3542
3543 UserGestureType gestureType = UserGestureType::Other;
3544 if (initialKeyEvent.windowsVirtualKeyCode() == VK_ESCAPE)
3545 gestureType = UserGestureType::EscapeKey;
3546
3547 UserGestureIndicator gestureIndicator(ProcessingUserGesture, m_frame.document(), gestureType, UserGestureIndicator::ProcessInteractionStyle::Delayed);
3548 UserTypingGestureIndicator typingGestureIndicator(m_frame);
3549
3550 // FIXME (bug 68185): this call should be made at another abstraction layer
3551 m_frame.loader().resetMultipleFormSubmissionProtection();
3552
3553 // In IE, access keys are special, they are handled after default keydown processing, but cannot be canceled - this is hard to match.
3554 // On Mac OS X, we process them before dispatching keydown, as the default keydown handler implements Emacs key bindings, which may conflict
3555 // with access keys. Then we dispatch keydown, but suppress its default handling.
3556 // On Windows, WebKit explicitly calls handleAccessKey() instead of dispatching a keypress event for WM_SYSCHAR messages.
3557 // Other platforms currently match either Mac or Windows behavior, depending on whether they send combined KeyDown events.
3558 bool matchedAnAccessKey = false;
3559 if (initialKeyEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::KeyDown)
3560 matchedAnAccessKey = handleAccessKey(initialKeyEvent);
3561
3562 // FIXME: it would be fair to let an input method handle KeyUp events before DOM dispatch.
3563 if (initialKeyEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::KeyUp || initialKeyEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::Char)
3564 return !element->dispatchKeyEvent(initialKeyEvent);
3565
3566 bool backwardCompatibilityMode = needsKeyboardEventDisambiguationQuirks();
3567
3568 PlatformKeyboardEvent keyDownEvent = initialKeyEvent;
3569 if (keyDownEvent.type() != PlatformEvent::RawKeyDown)
3570 keyDownEvent.disambiguateKeyDownEvent(PlatformEvent::RawKeyDown, backwardCompatibilityMode);
3571 auto keydown = KeyboardEvent::create(keyDownEvent, &m_frame.windowProxy());
3572 if (matchedAnAccessKey)
3573 keydown->preventDefault();
3574 keydown->setTarget(element);
3575
3576 auto setHasFocusVisibleIfNeeded = [initialKeyEvent, keydown](Element& element) {
3577 // If the user interacts with the page via the keyboard, the currently focused element should match :focus-visible.
3578 // Just typing a modifier key is not considered user interaction with the page, but Shift + a (or Caps Lock + a) is considered an interaction.
3579 bool userHasInteractedViaKeyword = keydown->modifierKeys().isEmpty() || ((keydown->shiftKey() || keydown->capsLockKey()) && !initialKeyEvent.text().isEmpty());
3580
3581 if (element.focused() && userHasInteractedViaKeyword)
3582 element.setHasFocusVisible(true);
3583 };
3584 setHasFocusVisibleIfNeeded(*element);
3585
3586 if (initialKeyEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::RawKeyDown) {
3587 element->dispatchEvent(keydown);
3588 // If frame changed as a result of keydown dispatch, then return true to avoid sending a subsequent keypress message to the new frame.
3589 bool changedFocusedFrame = m_frame.page() && &m_frame != &m_frame.page()->focusController().focusedOrMainFrame();
3590 return keydown->defaultHandled() || keydown->defaultPrevented() || changedFocusedFrame;
3591 }
3592
3593 // Run input method in advance of DOM event handling. This may result in the IM
3594 // modifying the page prior the keydown event, but this behaviour is necessary
3595 // in order to match IE:
3596 // 1. preventing default handling of keydown and keypress events has no effect on IM input;
3597 // 2. if an input method handles the event, its keyCode is set to 229 in keydown event.
3598 m_frame.editor().handleInputMethodKeydown(keydown.get());
3599
3600 bool handledByInputMethod = keydown->defaultHandled();
3601
3602 if (handledByInputMethod) {
3603 keyDownEvent.setWindowsVirtualKeyCode(CompositionEventKeyCode);
3604 keydown = KeyboardEvent::create(keyDownEvent, &m_frame.windowProxy());
3605 keydown->setTarget(element);
3606 keydown->setIsDefaultEventHandlerIgnored();
3607 }
3608
3609 if (accessibilityPreventsEventPropagation(keydown))
3610 keydown->stopPropagation();
3611
3612#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3613 DeferDOMTimersForScope deferralScope { m_frame.document()->quirks().needsDeferKeyDownAndKeyPressTimersUntilNextEditingCommand() };
3614#endif
3615
3616 element->dispatchEvent(keydown);
3617 if (handledByInputMethod) {
3618 m_frame.editor().didDispatchInputMethodKeydown(keydown.get());
3619 return true;
3620 }
3621
3622 // If frame changed as a result of keydown dispatch, then return early to avoid sending a subsequent keypress message to the new frame.
3623 bool changedFocusedFrame = m_frame.page() && &m_frame != &m_frame.page()->focusController().focusedOrMainFrame();
3624 bool keydownResult = keydown->defaultHandled() || keydown->defaultPrevented() || changedFocusedFrame;
3625 if (keydownResult && !backwardCompatibilityMode)
3626 return keydownResult;
3627
3628 // Focus may have changed during keydown handling, so refetch element.
3629 // But if we are dispatching a fake backward compatibility keypress, then we pretend that the keypress happened on the original element.
3630 if (!keydownResult) {
3631 element = eventTargetElementForDocument(m_frame.document());
3632 if (!element)
3633 return false;
3634 setHasFocusVisibleIfNeeded(*element);
3635 }
3636
3637 PlatformKeyboardEvent keyPressEvent = initialKeyEvent;
3638 keyPressEvent.disambiguateKeyDownEvent(PlatformEvent::Char, backwardCompatibilityMode);
3639 if (keyPressEvent.text().isEmpty())
3640 return keydownResult;
3641 auto keypress = KeyboardEvent::create(keyPressEvent, &m_frame.windowProxy());
3642 keypress->setTarget(element);
3643 if (keydownResult)
3644 keypress->preventDefault();
3645#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
3646 keypress->keypressCommands() = keydown->keypressCommands();
3647#endif
3648 element->dispatchEvent(keypress);
3649
3650 return keydownResult || keypress->defaultPrevented() || keypress->defaultHandled();
3651}
3652
3653static FocusDirection focusDirectionForKey(const AtomString& keyIdentifier)
3654{
3655 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> Down("Down", AtomString::ConstructFromLiteral);
3656 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> Up("Up", AtomString::ConstructFromLiteral);
3657 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> Left("Left", AtomString::ConstructFromLiteral);
3658 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> Right("Right", AtomString::ConstructFromLiteral);
3659
3660 FocusDirection retVal = FocusDirection::None;
3661
3662 if (keyIdentifier == Down)
3663 retVal = FocusDirection::Down;
3664 else if (keyIdentifier == Up)
3665 retVal = FocusDirection::Up;
3666 else if (keyIdentifier == Left)
3667 retVal = FocusDirection::Left;
3668 else if (keyIdentifier == Right)
3669 retVal = FocusDirection::Right;
3670
3671 return retVal;
3672}
3673
3674static void setInitialKeyboardSelection(Frame& frame, SelectionDirection direction)
3675{
3676 Document* document = frame.document();
3677 if (!document)
3678 return;
3679
3680 FrameSelection& selection = frame.selection();
3681
3682 if (!selection.isNone())
3683 return;
3684
3685 Element* focusedElement = document->focusedElement();
3686 VisiblePosition visiblePosition;
3687
3688 switch (direction) {
3689 case SelectionDirection::Backward:
3690 case SelectionDirection::Left:
3691 if (focusedElement)
3692 visiblePosition = VisiblePosition(positionBeforeNode(focusedElement));
3693 else
3694 visiblePosition = endOfDocument(document);
3695 break;
3696 case SelectionDirection::Forward:
3697 case SelectionDirection::Right:
3698 if (focusedElement)
3699 visiblePosition = VisiblePosition(positionAfterNode(focusedElement));
3700 else
3701 visiblePosition = startOfDocument(document);
3702 break;
3703 }
3704
3705 AXTextStateChangeIntent intent(AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionMove, AXTextSelection { AXTextSelectionDirectionDiscontiguous, AXTextSelectionGranularityUnknown, false });
3706 selection.setSelection(visiblePosition, FrameSelection::defaultSetSelectionOptions(UserTriggered), intent);
3707}
3708
3709static void handleKeyboardSelectionMovement(Frame& frame, KeyboardEvent& event)
3710{
3711 FrameSelection& selection = frame.selection();
3712
3713 bool isCommanded = event.getModifierState("Meta");
3714 bool isOptioned = event.getModifierState("Alt");
3715 bool isSelection = !selection.isNone();
3716
3717 FrameSelection::EAlteration alternation = event.getModifierState("Shift") ? FrameSelection::AlterationExtend : FrameSelection::AlterationMove;
3718 SelectionDirection direction = SelectionDirection::Forward;
3719 TextGranularity granularity = TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity;
3720
3721 switch (focusDirectionForKey(event.keyIdentifier())) {
3722 case FocusDirection::None:
3723 return;
3724 case FocusDirection::Forward:
3725 case FocusDirection::Backward:
3726 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3727 return;
3728 case FocusDirection::Up:
3729 direction = SelectionDirection::Backward;
3730 granularity = isCommanded ? TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary : TextGranularity::LineGranularity;
3731 break;
3732 case FocusDirection::Down:
3733 direction = SelectionDirection::Forward;
3734 granularity = isCommanded ? TextGranularity::DocumentBoundary : TextGranularity::LineGranularity;
3735 break;
3736 case FocusDirection::Left:
3737 direction = SelectionDirection::Left;
3738 granularity = (isCommanded) ? TextGranularity::LineBoundary : (isOptioned) ? TextGranularity::WordGranularity : TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity;
3739 break;
3740 case FocusDirection::Right:
3741 direction = SelectionDirection::Right;
3742 granularity = (isCommanded) ? TextGranularity::LineBoundary : (isOptioned) ? TextGranularity::WordGranularity : TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity;
3743 break;
3744 }
3745
3746 if (isSelection)
3747 selection.modify(alternation, direction, granularity, UserTriggered);
3748 else
3749 setInitialKeyboardSelection(frame, direction);
3750
3751 event.setDefaultHandled();
3752}

3762bool EventHandler::accessibilityPreventsEventPropagation(KeyboardEvent& event)
3763{
3764#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
3765 if (!AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnhancedUserInterfaceEnabled())
3766 return false;
3767
3768 if (!m_frame.settings().preventKeyboardDOMEventDispatch())
3769 return false;
3770
3771 // Check for key events that are relevant to accessibility: tab and arrows keys that change focus
3772 if (event.keyIdentifier() == "U+0009")
3773 return true;
3774 FocusDirection direction = focusDirectionForKey(event.keyIdentifier());
3775 if (direction != FocusDirection::None)
3776 return true;
3777#else
3778 UNUSED_PARAM(event);
3779#endif
3780 return false;
3781}

3783void EventHandler::defaultKeyboardEventHandler(KeyboardEvent& event)
3784{
3785 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
3786
3787 if (event.type() == eventNames().keydownEvent) {
3788 m_frame.editor().handleKeyboardEvent(event);
3789 if (event.defaultHandled())
3790 return;
3791 if (event.keyIdentifier() == "U+0009")
3792 defaultTabEventHandler(event);
3793 else if (event.keyIdentifier() == "U+0008")
3794 defaultBackspaceEventHandler(event);
3795 else {
3796 FocusDirection direction = focusDirectionForKey(event.keyIdentifier());
3797 if (direction != FocusDirection::None)
3798 defaultArrowEventHandler(direction, event);
3799 }
3800
3801 handleKeyboardSelectionMovementForAccessibility(event);
3802 }
3803 if (event.type() == eventNames().keypressEvent) {
3804 m_frame.editor().handleKeyboardEvent(event);
3805 if (event.defaultHandled())
3806 return;
3807 if (event.charCode() == ' ')
3808 defaultSpaceEventHandler(event);
3809 }

3812#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
3813bool EventHandler::dragHysteresisExceeded(const IntPoint& floatDragViewportLocation) const
3814{
3815 FloatPoint dragViewportLocation(floatDragViewportLocation.x(), floatDragViewportLocation.y());
3816 return dragHysteresisExceeded(dragViewportLocation);
3817}
3818
3819bool EventHandler::dragHysteresisExceeded(const FloatPoint& dragViewportLocation) const
3820{
3821 auto dragOperation = dragState().type.toSingleValue();
3822 ASSERT(dragOperation);
3823 int threshold = GeneralDragHysteresis;
3824 if (dragOperation) {
3825 switch (*dragOperation) {
3826 case DragSourceAction::Selection:
3827 threshold = TextDragHysteresis;
3828 break;
3829 case DragSourceAction::Image:
3830#if ENABLE(ATTACHMENT_ELEMENT)
3831 case DragSourceAction::Attachment:
3832#endif
3833 threshold = ImageDragHysteresis;
3834 break;
3835 case DragSourceAction::Link:
3836 threshold = LinkDragHysteresis;
3837 break;
3838#if ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
3839 case DragSourceAction::Color:
3840 threshold = ColorDragHystersis;
3841 break;
3842#endif
3843 case DragSourceAction::DHTML:
3844 break;
3845 }
3846 }
3847
3848 return mouseMovementExceedsThreshold(dragViewportLocation, threshold);
3849}

3853 if (!dragState().dataTransfer)
3854 return;

3856 dragState().dataTransfer = nullptr;

3903void EventHandler::dragSourceEndedAt(const PlatformMouseEvent& event, OptionSet<DragOperation> dragOperationMask, MayExtendDragSession mayExtendDragSession)
3904{
3905 // Send a hit test request so that RenderLayer gets a chance to update the :hover and :active pseudoclasses.
3906 prepareMouseEvent(OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> { HitTestRequest::Type::Release, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent }, event);

3909 dragState().dataTransfer->setDestinationOperationMask(dragOperationMask);

3954
3955bool EventHandler::handleDrag(const MouseEventWithHitTestResults& event, CheckDragHysteresis checkDragHysteresis)
3956{
3957 if (event.event().button() != LeftButton || event.event().type() != PlatformEvent::MouseMoved) {
3958 // If we allowed the other side of the bridge to handle a drag
3959 // last time, then m_mousePressed might still be set. So we
3960 // clear it now to make sure the next move after a drag
3961 // doesn't look like a drag.
3962 m_mousePressed = false;
3963 return false;
3964 }
3965
3966 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
3967
3968 if (eventLoopHandleMouseDragged(event))
3969 return true;
3970
3971 // Careful that the drag starting logic stays in sync with eventMayStartDrag().
3972 if (m_mouseDownMayStartDrag && !dragState().source) {
3973 dragState().shouldDispatchEvents = updateDragSourceActionsAllowed().contains(DragSourceAction::DHTML);
3974
3975 // Try to find an element that wants to be dragged.
3976 HitTestResult result(m_mouseDownContentsPosition);
3977 m_frame.document()->hitTest(OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent }, result);
3978 if (m_frame.page())
3979 dragState().source = m_frame.page()->dragController().draggableElement(&m_frame, result.targetElement(), m_mouseDownContentsPosition, dragState());
3980
3981 if (!dragState().source)
3982 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = false; // no element is draggable
3983 else
3984 m_dragMayStartSelectionInstead = dragState().type.contains(DragSourceAction::Selection);
3985 }
3986
3987 // For drags starting in the selection, the user must wait between the mousedown and mousedrag,
3988 // or else we bail on the dragging stuff and allow selection to occur
3989 if (m_mouseDownMayStartDrag && m_dragMayStartSelectionInstead && dragState().type.contains(DragSourceAction::Selection) && event.event().timestamp() - m_mouseDownTimestamp < TextDragDelay) {
3990 ASSERT(event.event().type() == PlatformEvent::MouseMoved);
3991 if (dragState().type.contains(DragSourceAction::Image)) {
3992 // ... unless the mouse is over an image, then we start dragging just the image
3993 dragState().type = DragSourceAction::Image;
3994 } else if (!dragState().type.containsAny({ DragSourceAction::DHTML, DragSourceAction::Link })) {
3995 // ... but only bail if we're not over an unselectable element.
3996 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = false;
3997 dragState().source = nullptr;
3998 // ... but if this was the first click in the window, we don't even want to start selection
3999 if (eventActivatedView(event.event()))
4000 m_mouseDownMayStartSelect = false;
4001 } else {
4002 // Prevent the following case from occuring:
4003 // 1. User starts a drag immediately after mouse down over an unselectable element.
4004 // 2. We enter this block and decided that since we're over an unselectable element, don't cancel the drag.
4005 // 3. The drag gets resolved as a potential selection drag below /but/ we haven't exceeded the drag hysteresis yet.
4006 // 4. We enter this block again, and since it's now marked as a selection drag, we cancel the drag.
4007 m_dragMayStartSelectionInstead = false;
4008 }
4009 }
4010
4011 if (!m_mouseDownMayStartDrag)
4012 return !mouseDownMayStartSelect() && !m_mouseDownMayStartAutoscroll;
4013 ASSERT(dragState().source);
4014
4015 if (!dragState().type.hasExactlyOneBitSet()) {
4016 ASSERT(dragState().type.contains(DragSourceAction::Selection));
4017#ifndef NDEBUG
4018 auto actionMaskCopy = dragState().type;
4019 actionMaskCopy.remove(DragSourceAction::Selection);
4020 ASSERT(actionMaskCopy.hasExactlyOneBitSet());
4021#endif
4022
4023 dragState().type = DragSourceAction::Selection;
4024 }
4025
4026 // We are starting a text/image/url drag, so the cursor should be an arrow
4027 if (FrameView* view = m_frame.view()) {
4028 // FIXME <rdar://7577595>: Custom cursors aren't supported during drag and drop (default to pointer).
4029 view->setCursor(pointerCursor());
4030 }
4031
4032 if (checkDragHysteresis == ShouldCheckDragHysteresis && !dragHysteresisExceeded(event.event().position()))
4033 return true;
4034
4035 // Once we're past the hysteresis point, we don't want to treat this gesture as a click
4036 invalidateClick();
4037
4038 OptionSet<DragOperation> sourceOperationMask;
4039
4040 // This does work only if we missed a dragEnd. Do it anyway, just to make sure the old dataTransfer gets numbed.
4041 // FIXME: Consider doing this earlier in this function as the earliest point we're sure it would be safe to drop an old drag.
4042 invalidateDataTransfer();
4043
4044 if (!m_frame.document())
4045 return false;
4046
4047 dragState().dataTransfer = DataTransfer::createForDrag(*m_frame.document());
4048 auto hasNonDefaultPasteboardData = HasNonDefaultPasteboardData::No;
4049
4050 if (dragState().shouldDispatchEvents) {
4051 ASSERT(dragState().source);
4052 auto dragStartDataTransfer = DataTransfer::createForDragStartEvent(dragState().source->document());
4053 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = dispatchDragStartEventOnSourceElement(dragStartDataTransfer);
4054 if (downcast<StaticPasteboard>(dragStartDataTransfer->pasteboard()).hasNonDefaultData())
4055 hasNonDefaultPasteboardData = HasNonDefaultPasteboardData::Yes;
4056 dragState().dataTransfer->moveDragState(WTFMove(dragStartDataTransfer));
4057
4058 if (dragState().source && dragState().type == DragSourceAction::DHTML && !dragState().dataTransfer->hasDragImage()) {
4059 dragState().source->document().updateStyleIfNeeded();
4060 if (auto* renderer = dragState().source->renderer()) {
4061 auto absolutePosition = renderer->localToAbsolute();
4062 auto delta = m_mouseDownContentsPosition - roundedIntPoint(absolutePosition);
4063 dragState().dataTransfer->setDragImage(*dragState().source, delta.width(), delta.height());
4064 } else {
4065 dispatchEventToDragSourceElement(eventNames().dragendEvent, event.event());
4066 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = false;
4067 invalidateDataTransfer();
4068 dragState().source = nullptr;
4069 return true;
4070 }
4071 }
4072
4073 dragState().dataTransfer->makeInvalidForSecurity();
4074
4075 if (m_mouseDownMayStartDrag) {
4076 // Gather values from DHTML element, if it set any.
4077 sourceOperationMask = dragState().dataTransfer->sourceOperationMask();
4078
4079 // Yuck, a draggedImage:moveTo: message can be fired as a result of kicking off the
4080 // drag with dragImage! Because of that reentrancy, we may think we've not
4081 // started the drag when that happens. So we have to assume it's started before we kick it off.
4082 dragState().dataTransfer->setDragHasStarted();
4083 }
4084 }
4085
4086 if (m_mouseDownMayStartDrag) {
4087 Page* page = m_frame.page();
4088 m_didStartDrag = page && page->dragController().startDrag(m_frame, dragState(), sourceOperationMask, event.event(), m_mouseDownContentsPosition, hasNonDefaultPasteboardData);
4089 // In WebKit2 we could re-enter this code and start another drag.
4090 // On OS X this causes problems with the ownership of the pasteboard and the promised types.
4091 if (m_didStartDrag) {
4092 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = false;
4093 return true;
4094 }
4095 if (shouldDispatchEventsToDragSourceElement()) {
4096 // Drag was canned at the last minute. We owe dragSource a dragend event.
4097 dispatchEventToDragSourceElement(eventNames().dragendEvent, event.event());
4098 m_mouseDownMayStartDrag = false;
4099 }
4100 }
4101
4102 if (!m_mouseDownMayStartDrag) {
4103 // Something failed to start the drag, clean up.
4104 invalidateDataTransfer();
4105 dragState().source = nullptr;
4106 }
4107
4108 // No more default handling (like selection), whether we're past the hysteresis bounds or not
4109 return true;
4110}
4111#endif // ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)

4113bool EventHandler::mouseMovementExceedsThreshold(const FloatPoint& viewportLocation, int pointsThreshold) const
4114{
4115 FrameView* view = m_frame.view();
4116 if (!view)
4117 return false;
4118 IntPoint location = view->windowToContents(flooredIntPoint(viewportLocation));
4119 IntSize delta = location - m_mouseDownContentsPosition;
4120
4121 return abs(delta.width()) >= pointsThreshold || abs(delta.height()) >= pointsThreshold;
4122}

4124bool EventHandler::handleTextInputEvent(const String& text, Event* underlyingEvent, TextEventInputType inputType)
4125{
4126 LOG(Editing, "EventHandler %p handleTextInputEvent (text %s)", this, text.utf8().data());
4127
4128 // Platforms should differentiate real commands like selectAll from text input in disguise (like insertNewline),
4129 // and avoid dispatching text input events from keydown default handlers.
4130 ASSERT(!is<KeyboardEvent>(underlyingEvent) || downcast<KeyboardEvent>(*underlyingEvent).type() == eventNames().keypressEvent);
4131
4132 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
4133
4134 EventTarget* target;
4135 if (underlyingEvent)
4136 target = underlyingEvent->target();
4137 else
4138 target = eventTargetElementForDocument(m_frame.document());
4139 if (!target)
4140 return false;
4141
4142 auto event = TextEvent::create(&m_frame.windowProxy(), text, inputType);
4143 event->setUnderlyingEvent(underlyingEvent);
4144
4145 target->dispatchEvent(event);
4146 return event->defaultHandled();
4147}

4185void EventHandler::defaultSpaceEventHandler(KeyboardEvent& event)
4186{
4187 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
4188
4189 ASSERT(event.type() == eventNames().keypressEvent);
4190
4191 if (event.ctrlKey() || event.metaKey() || event.altKey() || event.altGraphKey())
4192 return;
4193
4194 ScrollLogicalDirection direction = event.shiftKey() ? ScrollBlockDirectionBackward : ScrollBlockDirectionForward;
4195 if (logicalScrollOverflow(direction, ScrollByPage)) {
4196 event.setDefaultHandled();
4197 return;
4198 }
4199
4200 FrameView* view = m_frame.view();
4201 if (!view)
4202 return;
4203
4204 bool defaultHandled = m_frame.settings().eventHandlerDrivenSmoothKeyboardScrollingEnabled() ? handleKeyboardScrolling(event) : view->logicalScroll(direction, ScrollByPage);
4205 if (defaultHandled)
4206 event.setDefaultHandled();
4207}

4209void EventHandler::defaultBackspaceEventHandler(KeyboardEvent& event)
4210{
4211 ASSERT(event.type() == eventNames().keydownEvent);
4212
4213 if (event.ctrlKey() || event.metaKey() || event.altKey() || event.altGraphKey())
4214 return;
4215
4216 if (!m_frame.editor().behavior().shouldNavigateBackOnBackspace())
4217 return;
4218
4219 Page* page = m_frame.page();
4220 if (!page)
4221 return;
4222
4223 if (!m_frame.settings().backspaceKeyNavigationEnabled())
4224 return;
4225
4226 bool handledEvent = false;
4227
4228 if (event.shiftKey())
4229 handledEvent = page->backForward().goForward();
4230 else
4231 handledEvent = page->backForward().goBack();
4232
4233 if (handledEvent)
4234 event.setDefaultHandled();
4235}

4237float EventHandler::scrollDistance(ScrollDirection direction, ScrollGranularity granularity)
4238{
4239 auto scrollbar = [&] {
4240 if (direction == ScrollDirection::ScrollUp || direction == ScrollDirection::ScrollDown)
4241 return m_frame.view()->verticalScrollbar();
4242 return m_frame.view()->horizontalScrollbar();
4243 }();
4244
4245 switch (granularity) {
4246 case ScrollGranularity::ScrollByLine:
4247 return scrollbar->lineStep();
4248 case ScrollGranularity::ScrollByPage:
4249 return scrollbar->pageStep();
4250 case ScrollGranularity::ScrollByDocument:
4251 return scrollbar->totalSize();
4252 case ScrollGranularity::ScrollByPixel:
4253 return scrollbar->pixelStep();
4254 }
4255
4256 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4257}
4258
4259bool EventHandler::handleKeyboardScrolling(KeyboardEvent& event)
4260{
4261 // FIXME (bug 227459): This logic does not account for writing-mode.
4262
4263 enum class Key : uint8_t { LeftArrow, RightArrow, UpArrow, DownArrow, Space };
4264
4265 Key key;
4266 if (event.keyIdentifier() == "Left")
4267 key = Key::LeftArrow;
4268 else if (event.keyIdentifier() == "Right")
4269 key = Key::RightArrow;
4270 else if (event.keyIdentifier() == "Up")
4271 key = Key::UpArrow;
4272 else if (event.keyIdentifier() == "Down")
4273 key = Key::DownArrow;
4274 else if (event.charCode() == ' ')
4275 key = Key::Space;
4276 else
4277 return false;
4278
4279 auto granularity = [&] {
4280 switch (key) {
4281 case Key::LeftArrow:
4282 case Key::RightArrow:
4283 return event.altKey() ? ScrollGranularity::ScrollByPage : ScrollGranularity::ScrollByLine;
4284 case Key::UpArrow:
4285 case Key::DownArrow:
4286 if (event.metaKey())
4287 return ScrollGranularity::ScrollByDocument;
4288 if (event.altKey())
4289 return ScrollGranularity::ScrollByPage;
4290 return ScrollGranularity::ScrollByLine;
4291 case Key::Space:
4292 return ScrollGranularity::ScrollByPage;
4293 };
4294 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4295 }();
4296
4297 auto direction = [&] {
4298 switch (key) {
4299 case Key::LeftArrow:
4300 return ScrollDirection::ScrollLeft;
4301 case Key::RightArrow:
4302 return ScrollDirection::ScrollRight;
4303 case Key::UpArrow:
4304 return ScrollDirection::ScrollUp;
4305 case Key::DownArrow:
4306 return ScrollDirection::ScrollDown;
4307 case Key::Space:
4308 return event.shiftKey() ? ScrollDirection::ScrollUp : ScrollDirection::ScrollDown;
4309 }
4310 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4311 }();
4312
4313 return EventHandler::scrollRecursively(direction, granularity, nullptr);
4314}

4316void EventHandler::defaultArrowEventHandler(FocusDirection focusDirection, KeyboardEvent& event)
4317{
4318 ASSERT(event.type() == eventNames().keydownEvent);
4319
4320 if (!isSpatialNavigationEnabled(&m_frame)) {
4321 if (m_frame.settings().eventHandlerDrivenSmoothKeyboardScrollingEnabled())
4322 handleKeyboardScrolling(event);

4327 return;

4334 // mode editing.
4335 if (m_frame.document()->inDesignMode())
4336 return;

4339 event.setDefaultHandled();

4446
4447bool EventHandler::handleTouchEvent(const PlatformTouchEvent& event)
4448{
4449 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
4450
4451 // First build up the lists to use for the 'touches', 'targetTouches' and 'changedTouches' attributes
4452 // in the JS event. See http://www.sitepen.com/blog/2008/07/10/touching-and-gesturing-on-the-iphone/
4453 // for an overview of how these lists fit together.
4454
4455 // Holds the complete set of touches on the screen and will be used as the 'touches' list in the JS event.
4456 RefPtr<TouchList> touches = TouchList::create();
4457
4458 // A different view on the 'touches' list above, filtered and grouped by event target. Used for the
4459 // 'targetTouches' list in the JS event.
4460 typedef HashMap<EventTarget*, RefPtr<TouchList>> TargetTouchesMap;
4461 TargetTouchesMap touchesByTarget;
4462
4463 // Array of touches per state, used to assemble the 'changedTouches' list in the JS event.
4464 typedef HashSet<RefPtr<EventTarget>> EventTargetSet;
4465 struct {
4466 // The touches corresponding to the particular change state this struct instance represents.
4467 RefPtr<TouchList> m_touches;
4468 // Set of targets involved in m_touches.
4469 EventTargetSet m_targets;
4470 } changedTouches[PlatformTouchPoint::TouchStateEnd];
4471
4472 const Vector<PlatformTouchPoint>& points = event.touchPoints();
4473
4474 UserGestureIndicator gestureIndicator(ProcessingUserGesture, m_frame.document());
4475
4476 bool freshTouchEvents = true;
4477 bool allTouchReleased = true;
4478 for (auto& point : points) {
4479 if (point.state() != PlatformTouchPoint::TouchPressed)
4480 freshTouchEvents = false;
4481 if (point.state() != PlatformTouchPoint::TouchReleased && point.state() != PlatformTouchPoint::TouchCancelled)
4482 allTouchReleased = false;
4483 }
4484
4485 for (auto& point : points) {
4486 PlatformTouchPoint::State pointState = point.state();
4487 LayoutPoint pagePoint = documentPointForWindowPoint(m_frame, point.pos());
4488
4489 OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::TouchEvent };
4490 // The HitTestRequest types used for mouse events map quite adequately
4491 // to touch events. Note that in addition to meaning that the hit test
4492 // should affect the active state of the current node if necessary,
4493 // HitTestRequest::Type::Active signifies that the hit test is taking place
4494 // with the mouse (or finger in this case) being pressed.
4495 switch (pointState) {
4496 case PlatformTouchPoint::TouchPressed:
4497 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::Active);
4498 break;
4499 case PlatformTouchPoint::TouchMoved:
4500 hitType.add({ HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::Move, HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly });
4501 break;
4502 case PlatformTouchPoint::TouchReleased:
4503 case PlatformTouchPoint::TouchCancelled:
4504 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::Release);
4505 break;
4506 case PlatformTouchPoint::TouchStationary:
4507 hitType.add({ HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly });
4508 break;
4509 default:
4510 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4511 break;
4512 }
4513
4514 if (shouldGesturesTriggerActive())
4515 hitType.add(HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly);
4516
4517 // Increment the platform touch id by 1 to avoid storing a key of 0 in the hashmap.
4518 unsigned touchPointTargetKey = point.id() + 1;
4519 RefPtr<EventTarget> touchTarget;
4520 if (pointState == PlatformTouchPoint::TouchPressed) {
4521 HitTestResult result;
4522 if (freshTouchEvents) {
4523 result = hitTestResultAtPoint(pagePoint, hitType | HitTestRequest::Type::AllowChildFrameContent);
4524 m_originatingTouchPointTargetKey = touchPointTargetKey;
4525 } else if (m_originatingTouchPointDocument.get() && m_originatingTouchPointDocument->frame()) {
4526 LayoutPoint pagePointInOriginatingDocument = documentPointForWindowPoint(*m_originatingTouchPointDocument->frame(), point.pos());
4527 result = hitTestResultInFrame(m_originatingTouchPointDocument->frame(), pagePointInOriginatingDocument, hitType);
4528 if (!result.innerNode())
4529 continue;
4530 } else
4531 continue;
4532
4533 Element* element = result.targetElement();
4534 ASSERT(element);
4535
4536 if (element && InspectorInstrumentation::handleTouchEvent(m_frame, *element))
4537 return true;
4538
4539 Document& doc = element->document();
4540 // Record the originating touch document even if it does not have a touch listener.
4541 if (freshTouchEvents) {
4542 m_originatingTouchPointDocument = &doc;
4543 freshTouchEvents = false;
4544 }
4545 if (!doc.hasTouchEventHandlers())
4546 continue;
4547 m_originatingTouchPointTargets.set(touchPointTargetKey, element);
4548 touchTarget = element;
4549 } else if (pointState == PlatformTouchPoint::TouchReleased || pointState == PlatformTouchPoint::TouchCancelled) {
4550 // No need to perform a hit-test since we only need to unset :hover and :active states.
4551 if (!shouldGesturesTriggerActive() && allTouchReleased)
4552 m_frame.document()->updateHoverActiveState(hitType, 0);
4553 if (touchPointTargetKey == m_originatingTouchPointTargetKey)
4554 m_originatingTouchPointTargetKey = 0;
4555
4556 // The target should be the original target for this touch, so get it from the hashmap. As it's a release or cancel
4557 // we also remove it from the map.
4558 touchTarget = m_originatingTouchPointTargets.take(touchPointTargetKey);
4559 } else
4560 // No hittest is performed on move or stationary, since the target is not allowed to change anyway.
4561 touchTarget = m_originatingTouchPointTargets.get(touchPointTargetKey);
4562
4563 if (!is<Node>(touchTarget))
4564 continue;
4565 auto& document = downcast<Node>(*touchTarget).document();
4566 if (!document.hasTouchEventHandlers())
4567 continue;
4568 auto* targetFrame = document.frame();
4569 if (!targetFrame)
4570 continue;
4571
4572 if (&m_frame != targetFrame) {
4573 // pagePoint should always be relative to the target elements containing frame.
4574 pagePoint = documentPointForWindowPoint(*targetFrame, point.pos());
4575 }
4576
4577 float scaleFactor = targetFrame->pageZoomFactor() * targetFrame->frameScaleFactor();
4578
4579 int adjustedPageX = lroundf(pagePoint.x() / scaleFactor);
4580 int adjustedPageY = lroundf(pagePoint.y() / scaleFactor);
4581
4582 auto touch = Touch::create(targetFrame, touchTarget.get(), point.id(),
4583 point.screenPos().x(), point.screenPos().y(), adjustedPageX, adjustedPageY,
4584 point.radiusX(), point.radiusY(), point.rotationAngle(), point.force());
4585
4586 // Ensure this target's touch list exists, even if it ends up empty, so it can always be passed to TouchEvent::Create below.
4587 TargetTouchesMap::iterator targetTouchesIterator = touchesByTarget.find(touchTarget.get());
4588 if (targetTouchesIterator == touchesByTarget.end())
4589 targetTouchesIterator = touchesByTarget.set(touchTarget.get(), TouchList::create()).iterator;
4590
4591 // touches and targetTouches should only contain information about touches still on the screen, so if this point is
4592 // released or cancelled it will only appear in the changedTouches list.
4593 if (pointState != PlatformTouchPoint::TouchReleased && pointState != PlatformTouchPoint::TouchCancelled) {
4594 touches->append(touch.copyRef());
4595 targetTouchesIterator->value->append(touch.copyRef());
4596 }
4597
4598 // Now build up the correct list for changedTouches.
4599 // Note that any touches that are in the TouchStationary state (e.g. if
4600 // the user had several points touched but did not move them all) should
4601 // never be in the changedTouches list so we do not handle them explicitly here.
4602 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=37609 for further discussion
4603 // about the TouchStationary state.
4604 if (pointState != PlatformTouchPoint::TouchStationary) {
4605 ASSERT(pointState < PlatformTouchPoint::TouchStateEnd);
4606 if (!changedTouches[pointState].m_touches)
4607 changedTouches[pointState].m_touches = TouchList::create();
4608 changedTouches[pointState].m_touches->append(WTFMove(touch));
4609 changedTouches[pointState].m_targets.add(touchTarget);
4610 }
4611 }
4612 m_touchPressed = touches->length() > 0;
4613 if (allTouchReleased)
4614 m_originatingTouchPointDocument = nullptr;
4615
4616 // Now iterate the changedTouches list and m_targets within it, sending events to the targets as required.
4617 bool swallowedEvent = false;
4618 RefPtr<TouchList> emptyList = TouchList::create();
4619 for (unsigned state = 0; state != PlatformTouchPoint::TouchStateEnd; ++state) {
4620 if (!changedTouches[state].m_touches)
4621 continue;
4622
4623 // When sending a touch cancel event, use empty touches and targetTouches lists.
4624 bool isTouchCancelEvent = (state == PlatformTouchPoint::TouchCancelled);
4625 RefPtr<TouchList>& effectiveTouches(isTouchCancelEvent ? emptyList : touches);
4626 const AtomString& stateName(eventNameForTouchPointState(static_cast<PlatformTouchPoint::State>(state)));
4627
4628 for (auto& target : changedTouches[state].m_targets) {
4629 ASSERT(is<Node>(target));
4630
4631 RefPtr<TouchList> targetTouches(isTouchCancelEvent ? emptyList : touchesByTarget.get(target.get()));
4632 ASSERT(targetTouches);
4633
4634 Ref<TouchEvent> touchEvent = TouchEvent::create(effectiveTouches.get(), targetTouches.get(), changedTouches[state].m_touches.get(),
4635 stateName, downcast<Node>(*target).document().windowProxy(), { }, event.modifiers());
4636 target->dispatchEvent(touchEvent);
4637 swallowedEvent = swallowedEvent || touchEvent->defaultPrevented() || touchEvent->defaultHandled();
4638 }
4639 }
4640
4641 return swallowedEvent;
4642}

4646bool EventHandler::dispatchSyntheticTouchEventIfEnabled(const PlatformMouseEvent& platformMouseEvent)
4647{
4648#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
4649 UNUSED_PARAM(platformMouseEvent);
4650 return false;
4651#else
4652 if (!m_frame.settings().isTouchEventEmulationEnabled())
4653 return false;
4654
4655 PlatformEvent::Type eventType = platformMouseEvent.type();
4656 if (eventType != PlatformEvent::MouseMoved && eventType != PlatformEvent::MousePressed && eventType != PlatformEvent::MouseReleased)
4657 return false;
4658
4659 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent };
4660 MouseEventWithHitTestResults mouseEvent = prepareMouseEvent(hitType, platformMouseEvent);
4661 if (mouseEvent.scrollbar() || subframeForHitTestResult(mouseEvent))
4662 return false;
4663
4664 // The order is important. This check should follow the subframe test: http://webkit.org/b/111292.
4665 if (eventType == PlatformEvent::MouseMoved && !m_touchPressed)
4666 return true;
4667
4668 SyntheticSingleTouchEvent touchEvent(platformMouseEvent);
4669 return handleTouchEvent(touchEvent);
4670#endif
4671}
